(151, 1, '2017-03-15 21:18:49', '2017-03-15 21:18:49', '[et_pb_section fb_built="1" custom_padding="0px|||" admin_label="section"][et_pb_row use_custom_width="on" custom_width_percent="93%" custom_padding="|0px||0" background_color="#efefef"][et_pb_column type="1_4" parallax="off" parallax_method="on"][et_pb_image src="http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Promises-1.png" custom_margin="50px|||25px"][/et_pb_image][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="3_4" parallax="off" parallax_method="on"][et_pb_text][/et_pb_text][et_pb_text custom_margin="0px|20px|0px|0px" custom_padding="0px|0px|0px|0px"]<p>Based on the work done- which was evaluated after getting information from the government records, advisors, press releases, news reports and government officers, every promise except one which was too generic and difficult to assess was assigned one of the following status: ''Fulfilled'', ''Under Progress'', ''Yet to Start'', ''Stalled'', and ''Broken''. The key difference between ''Broken'' and &ldquo;Yet to Start'' is that if the government misses the timeline Aam Aadmi Party had proposed before the polls for a certain promise or has refused to fulfil its promise, then it is classified as ''Broken'', or else as ''Yet To Start''.</p>[/et_pb_text][et_pb_text][/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type="1_2" parallax="off" parallax_method="on"][et_pb_post_slider][/et_pb_post_slider][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_2" parallax="off" parallax_method="on"][et_pb_blurb url="http://manifesto.electionpromisestracker.in/"]<p><a class="embedly-card" href="http://manifesto.electionpromisestracker.in/">Election Promises</a><br />\n<script async="" src="//cdn.embedly.com/widgets/platform.js" charset="UTF-8"></script></p>\n[/et_pb_blurb][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section]', 'Home-Test', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '142-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-03-15 21:18:49', '2017-03-15 21:18:49', '', 142, 'http://www.electionp