(344, 1, '2017-05-14 03:04:49', '2017-05-13 21:34:49', '[et_pb_section bb_built="1" admin_label="section" custom_padding="0px|||"][et_pb_row admin_label="row" custom_padding="||0px|" background_color="#e8e8e8"][et_pb_column type="1_2"][et_pb_blurb admin_label="Blurb" image="http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Promises-1.png" text_orientation="right" custom_margin="||0px|" custom_padding="20px||0px|60px"]\n\n\n\n[/et_pb_blurb][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_2"][et_pb_text admin_label="Text" custom_margin="|||0px" custom_padding="20px|80px||0px"]\n\n</p><p><span style="font-size: medium;">In a democracy, the faith voters repose in their representatives and the political institutions is sacrosanct. It is this faith that keeps the democracy alive. Hence, preserving this faith becomes important.</span></p><p><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>Election Promises Tracker</strong> enables voters to monitor the performance of their governments. It will fact-check claims of the politicians and the governments. It will also assess if governments adhere to all of their promises in regard to education, health, law and order, minority rights, culture, human rights, and many more.</span></p><p>\n\n[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row admin_label="row"][et_pb_column type="1_2"][et_pb_post_slider admin_label="Post Slider" use_text_overlay="off" image_placement="top" use_bg_overlay="off"]\n\n\n\n[/et_pb_post_slider][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_2"][et_pb_blurb admin_label="Blurb" url="http://manifesto.electionpromisestracker.in/" header_font_size="40px" header_letter_spacing_last_edited="on|desktop" body_font="||||" body_font_size="15px" body_line_height="1.8em" custom_padding="|||"]\n\n</p><blockquote class="embedly-card"><h4><a href="http://manifesto.electionpromisestracker.in/">Manifesto Tracker</a></h4><p>Aam Aadmi Party surged to power with a decisive mandate of 67 seats out of 70 in February 2015. The Party called for alternative politics and made several commitments to the people of Delhi particularly in the field of education. Aam Aadmi Party has completed two years in governance on 14th February 2017.</p></blockquote><p><script async="" src="//cdn.embedly.com/widgets/platform.js" charset="UTF-8"></script><br />\n\n[/et_pb_blurb][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section]', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '142-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-14 03:04:49', '2017-05-13 21:34:49', '', 142, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/142-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
