(379, 1, '2017-05-17 12:15:31', '2017-05-17 06:45:31', 'Aam Aadmi Party surged to power with a decisive mandate of 67 seats out of 70 in February 2015. The Party called for alternative politics and made several commitments to the people of Delhi. Aam Aadmi Party has completed two years in governance on 14th February 2017.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nElection Promises Tracker is a citizen initiative that tracks governments’ performance against the promises the party made to the electorate in the fields of Education, Health, Governance, Transportation, Environment and Services like Energy, Water, Wi-Fi. The promises have, primarily, been taken from AAP''s Delhi 2015 Elections Manifesto which can be accessed <a href="http://www.aamaadmiparty.org/AAP-Manifesto-2015.pdf">here</a>. Please read our guidelines for categorization of promises <a href="http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/categorization-guidelines/">here</a>.\r\n\r\nWe are still in process of researching and reviewing the status of promises in other sectors and therefore present to you the status of AAP government’s performance against their education sector promises. Stay tuned!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWrite to anuragkundu@electionpromisestracker.in in case you observe any discrepancy and write to Joinus@electionpromisestracker.in to volunteer with us.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'delhi-government', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'delhi-government', '', '', '2017-06-01 12:07:49', '2017-06-01 06:37:49', '', 354, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?page_id=379', 0, 'page', '', 0),
