(392, 3, '2017-05-17 12:52:24', '2017-05-17 07:22:24', 'The BJP government’s ‘<a href="http://pmksy.gov.in/">Per Drop More Crop</a>’ initiative is focussed towards improving water use efficiency. The budgetary support for the scheme was Rs. 1550 crore in 2015-16, Rs. 1990 crore in 2016-17 and Rs. 3050 crore in 2017-18.\r\n\r\nThe ‘Per Drop More Crop’ initiative under the Pradhan Mantri Krishi Sinchayee Yojana is the successor to the <a href="https://www.google.co.in/url?sa=t&amp;rct=j&amp;q=&amp;esrc=s&amp;source=web&amp;cd=1&amp;cad=rja&amp;uact=8&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjA36elsfHTAhWJsI8KHSSiA-MQFgghMAA&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fmidh.gov.in%2FAtGlance%2FMI-AT-A-Glance.docx&amp;usg=AFQjCNEw0dN3zigsAPGZ52HxI3QZe5uncw&amp;sig2=bu0nEASpE9NQxilFzqX9BQ">Centrally Sponsored Scheme on Micro Irrigation (CSS)</a> launched by the UPA government in 2006.\r\n\r\nThe 2017-18 budget had a provision of micro irrigation fund with an initial corpus of Rs 5,000 crore.\r\nDuring 2016-17, 8.4 lakh hectares(ha.) area was covered under micro irrigation against a target of 10.5 lakh ha, <a href="http://pmksy.gov.in/microirrigation/Physical_Report.aspx">an achievement of 80%</a>. 80% of targets were achieved during 2015-16 as well. A total of  <a href="http://164.100.47.5/qsearch/qsearch.aspx">59 lakh hectares</a> has been covered under Micro Irrigation as of April 2017 including 15 lakh hectares under the current government.', 'Introduce and promote low water consuming irrigation techniques and optimum utilization of water resources', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'introduce-and-promote-low-water-consuming-irrigation-techniques-and-optimum-utilization-of-water-resources', '', '', '2017-05-19 13:43:18', '2017-05-19 08:13:18', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=392', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
(393, 3, '2017-05-17 12:53:15', '2017-05-17 07:23:15', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">The ‘zero defect , zero effect’ (ZED) scheme was launched in </span><a href="http://www.tribuneindia.com/news/punjab/community/pm-launches-national-sc-st-hub-zed-scheme-in-ludhiana/311368.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">October 2016</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. It is aimed to create a spirit of competition among enterprises for producing top quality products, as rated SMEs will get better business opportunities. The scheme plans to assist and rate 22,000 MSMEs on voluntary basis.  </span>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://164.100.47.5/newcommittee/reports/EnglishCommittees/Committee%20on%20Industry/280.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">No details</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> have been provided regarding availability of technological resources, institutional architecture, financial resources required or the parameters fixed for selection of the intended beneficiaries.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The official website doesn’t display any information regarding </span><a href="http://zed.org.in/awareness-and-training.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">trainings conducted</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> so far, or any information about how many </span><a href="http://www.zed.org.in/zed-certified-companies.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">certified MSMEs</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> are there.</span>\r\n\r\nSince no information has been provided to analyse the performance, this promise has been given the status of "Inadequate Progress".', 'Focus on Zero defect products', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'focus-on-zero-defect-products', '', '', '2017-05-27 15:31:02', '2017-05-27 10:01:02', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=393', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
(394, 3, '2017-05-17 12:53:50', '2017-05-17 07:23:50', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">No special courts have been set up to stop hoarding and black marketeering. No progress has been made with regard to the amendment making </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=107453"><span style="font-weight: 400;">hoarding a non-bailable offence</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">No strict measure has been initiated by the government. Their steps, thus far, are limited to issuing </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/mbErel.aspx?relid=121420"><span style="font-weight: 400;">advisories to State governments </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">for strict enforcement of essential Commodities Act, 1955, and the Prime Minister </span><a href="http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Set-up-special-courts-to-try-hoarders-PM-Narendra-Modi-tells-states/articleshow/37282089.cms"><span style="font-weight: 400;">urging</span></a> <span style="font-weight: 400;">the States to  set up special courts. </span>', 'Put in place strict measures and special courts to stop hoarding and black marketing', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'put-in-place-strict-measures-and-special-courts-to-stop-hoarding-and-black-marketing', '', '', '2017-05-19 14:29:35', '2017-05-19 08:59:35', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=394', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
