(410, 3, '2017-05-17 13:17:11', '2017-05-17 07:47:11', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">The BJP government introduced Sagarmala Project which will promote port-led direct and indirect development and to provide infrastructure to transport goods to and from ports quickly. It received </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=117691"><span style="font-weight: 400;">in-principle</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> approval of the Cabinet in March, 2015. The </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=138881"><span style="font-weight: 400;">National Perspective Plan</span></a> <span style="font-weight: 400;">detailing the contours of the project was released in April 2016.</span>\r\n\r\nRs. 390 crores have been released for 35 projects taken up in 2015-16 &amp;  2016-17 financial years.\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Rs.3,34,000 crores are needed from 2017-19, however, </span><a href="http://164.100.47.5/newcommittee/reports/EnglishCommittees/Committee%20on%20Transport,%20Tourism%20and%20Culture/247.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">details about financing of the project </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">are not yet clear.</span>\r\n\r\nSince only the approval &amp; funds have been released, there is no progress that has been seen on the ground. Hence, it has been given the status "Inadequate Progress".', 'Build world class Ports; connecting them with roads and rail to the hinterland so as to drive the maritime trade', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'build-world-class-ports-connecting-them-with-roads-and-rail-to-the-hinterland-so-as-to-drive-the-maritime-trade-of-the-country', '', '', '2017-05-27 17:37:16', '2017-05-27 12:07:16', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=410', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
