(434, 3, '2017-05-17 13:31:19', '2017-05-17 08:01:19', '<a href="https://www.ebasta.in/">E-Basta</a>, an app launched by the BJP government, is an app designed to reduce the burden of school bag of students and provide ease of access from anywhere. More than 1500 school level books are available on E-Basta.\r\n\r\nOnly <a href="http://img.asercentre.org/docs/Publications/ASER%20Reports/ASER%202016/Report%20sections/aser2016-nationalfindings.pdf">20% of schools</a> in India have access to a computer, according to a Pratham report published in 2016. The BJP government has allocated Rs. 311 crores for Computer Aided Learning during the 2016-17.\r\n\r\nNo framework has been published by the BJP government to integrate the app (E-basta) with the existing system in the absence of which the promise cannot be fulfilled. Therefore the performance against this promise has been classified as "Inadequate Progress".', 'Explore ways to reduce the daily burden of carrying books to school for children using technology', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'explore-ways-to-reduce-the-daily-burden-of-carrying-books-to-school-for-children-using-technology', '', '', '2017-05-19 16:45:11', '2017-05-19 11:15:11', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=434', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
(435, 3, '2017-05-17 13:28:42', '2017-05-17 07:58:42', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">India’s rank in </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">‘Ease of Doing Business</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;">’ improved from </span><a href="http://www.thehindu.com/business/Economy/India-up-one-position-in-WB-ease-of-business-ranking/article16081515.ece"><span style="font-weight: 400;">142nd rank in 2014</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to </span><a href="http://www.doingbusiness.org/rankings"><span style="font-weight: 400;">130th rank in 2016</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, according to World Bank.  This is an improvement of 12 places.  However, on the parameter of ‘</span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Starting A New Business</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;">’, India’s rank slipped to </span><a href="http://www.doingbusiness.org/rankings"><span style="font-weight: 400;">155th rank in 2016</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> compared to </span><a href="http://www.business-standard.com/article/economy-policy/india-moves-up-by-just-one-notch-on-world-bank-s-ease-of-doing-business-index-116102501493_1.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">151th rank in 2014</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">On the parameter of ‘</span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Getting Electricity</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;">’ , India’s rank has been </span><a href="http://164.100.47.194/Loksabha/Questions/QResult15.aspx?qref=50242&amp;lsno=16"><span style="font-weight: 400;">improved </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">from 137th rank in 2015 to 26th rank in 2016. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">The report has recognized the efforts of getting electricity in Delhi to make it faster and cheaper to obtain an electricity connection.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The government </span><a href="http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/economy/policy/industrial-licence-validity-extended-to-three-years/articleshow/37676645.cms"><span style="font-weight: 400;">extended</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> the validity of industrial licence to 3 years and the industrial licence for defence to 15 years in July, 2014.</span>', 'Will ensure that a conducive, enabling environment is created making ''doing business'' in India easy', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '432-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-17 13:28:42', '2017-05-17 07:58:42', '', 432, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/432-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(436, 3, '2017-05-17 13:30:16', '2017-05-17 08:00:16', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government has simplified the procedures in four areas only out of 11 indicators set by World Bank. These include </span><a href="http://www.doingbusiness.org/reforms/overview/economy/india"><span style="font-weight: 400;">paying taxes easier</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> by introducing electronic system for paying employees contributions, </span><a href="http://www.doingbusiness.org/reforms/overview/economy/india"><span style="font-weight: 400;">trading across borders</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> by means of single electronic gateway, simplifying </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">the process for getting an electricity connection by eliminating the internal wiring inspection by the Electrical Inspectorate </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">and the process of starting a new business </span><a href="http://www.businessmirror.com.ph/government-rolls-out-simplified-business-application-procedure-across-agencies/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">reducing</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> procedural requirement of 34 days to 8 days.</span>\r\n\r\nThere is still a lot of scope to simplify the procedures &amp; to remove the bottlenecks for making business easy. Hence, it has been given the status "Inadequate Progress".', 'Will ensure cutting the red tape, simplify the procedures & remove the bottlenecks', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'will-ensure-cutting-the-red-tape-simplify-the-procedures-remove-the-bottlenecks', '', '', '2017-05-27 17:47:22', '2017-05-27 12:17:22', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=436', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
(437, 3, '2017-05-17 13:30:26', '2017-05-17 08:00:26', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">Parliament passed</span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/printrelease.aspx?relid=148344"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Goods &amp; Services Tax Bill (GST)</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to </span><a href="http://indianexpress.com/article/business/companies/gst-rollout-to-boost-private-investment-say-industry-stalwarts-4573421/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">create</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> a hassle-free environment and boost up the investor’s confidence. The bill has been </span><a href="http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/president-gives-nod-to-four-supporting-legislations-on-gst/articleshow/58161786.cms"><span style="font-weight: 400;">given assent</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> by the president &amp; has been ratified by 21 states. The government is yet to notify the act. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The BJP government appointed a committee to recommend measures to simplify the </span><b>income tax</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> structures. The Committee submitted its</span> <a href="http://indianexpress.com/article/business/business-others/justice-r-v-easwar-panel-submits-2nd-report-on-i-t-laws-to-arun-jaitley-4452246/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">second report</span></a> <span style="font-weight: 400;">to the government in December 2016. However </span><a href="http://www.financialexpress.com/budget/union-budget-2017-pm-narendra-modi-misses-opportunity-for-big-bang-income-tax-reforms/532613/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">no major</span></a> <span style="font-weight: 400;">income tax reforms were announced in the budget in February 2017.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Implementation of the</span> <a href="http://www.newindianexpress.com/business/2017/jan/27/in-tax-clarity-bid-to-foreign-entities-general-anti-avoidance-rule-to-become-applicable-from-2017-1-1564096--1.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">General Anti-Avoidance Rule</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> (GAAR), a proposal of UPA government was getting delayed due to apprehensions on part of foreign investors. Following consultations, the Ministry of Finance operationalised the GAAR provisions </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=157712"><span style="font-weight: 400;">with effect from 1st April 2017.</span></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Contrary to the expectations of Minimum Alternative Tax (MAT) </span><a href="https://www.thequint.com/business/2016/02/25/remove-mat-bury-retrospective-taxes-india-inc-demands-capital-gains-tax"><span style="font-weight: 400;">removal</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> by industries, government says that it is not practical. However, Government has </span><a href="http://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/companies/union-budget-2017-18-fm-says-mat-removal-not-practical-ups-carry-forward-to-15-years-949959.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">extended</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> the period of time upto which it can be carried forward upto 15 years.It will enable companies </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">to off-set their future tax liabilities.</span>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">(Minimum Alternative Tax is a tax to felicitate taxation of those companies </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">which show zero or negligible income to avoid tax</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">)</span>', 'Rationalization and simplification of the tax regime  to remove uncertainty and create investor confidence', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'rationalization-and-simplification-of-the-tax-regime-to-remove-uncertainty-and-create-investor-confidence', '', '', '2017-05-19 14:33:55', '2017-05-19 09:03:55', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=437', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
