(492, 3, '2017-05-17 16:57:08', '2017-05-17 11:27:08', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">Banks are undercapitalised, out of 1.8 lakh crores </span><a href="http://www.firstpost.com/business/union-budget-2017-is-a-total-miss-on-banking-reforms-economy-will-pay-a-price-for-it-3243084.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">capital needed by government banks</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> under the Indradhanush Plan, BJP government has assured a total of 0.7 lakh crores over the four years till 2018-2019.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Non-Performing loans of Indian banking Industry </span><a href="http://www.livemint.com/Opinion/sk1O8BoOUyTssUcSnNQw5I/Dear-finance-minister-where-is-banking-sector-reform.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">rose</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to 9.1% in December as compared to 7.8 % in March, 2016..</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Reserve Bank of India(RBI) has permitted 11 companies  to set up </span><a href="http://www.firstpost.com/business/ril-aditya-birla-et-al-getting-payment-bank-licences-what-it-means-for-the-indias-banking-sector-2399840.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">payment banks</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to ease the use of banking and to reach more people. </span>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Cyber Appellate, the go-to body for victims of cyber crime or online fraud, has been</span><a href="http://indianexpress.com/article/india/cyber-appellate-tribunal-chiefs-post-lying-vacant-since-last-five-years-4426644/"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> functioning </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">without a chairperson</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> since 2011. </span>', 'Undertake Banking reforms to enhance ease and access, as well as accountability', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '490-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-17 16:57:08', '2017-05-17 11:27:08', '', 490, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/490-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(493, 3, '2017-05-17 16:57:12', '2017-05-17 11:27:12', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">No bill in this regard has been tabled in Parliament since BJP government has come to power. However, the ministry </span><a href="http://www.moef.nic.in/sites/default/files/ScanJobInvitation%20of%20comments%20Draft%20Environment%20Law.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">drafted</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> a bill in this regard and uploaded on its website in October 2015 but no progress has been made since then. </span>', 'Frame the environment laws in a manner that provides no scope for confusion and will lead to speedy clearance of proposals without delay', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '484-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-17 16:57:12', '2017-05-17 11:27:12', '', 484, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/484-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(494, 3, '2017-05-17 16:59:04', '2017-05-17 11:29:04', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">Contrary to the </span><a href="http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/one-crore-jobs-if-bjp-comes-to-power-narendra-modi/articleshow/26165012.cms"><span style="font-weight: 400;">promise</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> of 1 crore jobs , a  total number of </span><a href="http://www.hindustantimes.com/india/job-growth-in-8-sectors-at-7-year-low-govt-data/story-UkWVLA9jQyZJZuNCWXI3BO.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">1.35 lakh jobs</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in 2015 &amp; </span><a href="http://www.firstpost.com/business/where-are-the-jobs-only-2-31-lakh-added-in-2016-when-10-15-lakh-youth-enter-job-market-each-month-3411354.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">2.31 lakh jobs</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in 2016 have been created in 8 labour-intensive manufacturing sectors  as compared to 4.21 lakh jobs in 2014. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">India Manufacturing (</span><a href="https://www.markiteconomics.com/Survey/PressRelease.mvc/66876750e4214599a04573a9b7634d6a"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Purchasing Managers’ Index</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">)PMI fell below 50 in December, 2016. It has not crossed the mark of 55 since 2012. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">(</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Purchasing Managers'' Index (PMI) is an indicator of the economic health of the manufacturing sector. The </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">PMI</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is based on five major indicators: new orders, inventory levels, production, supplier </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">deliveries</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and the employment environment.)</span>\r\n\r\nDespite of the Flagship schemes like Skill-India &amp; Make in India, BJP government has failed to create enough jobs. Hence, this promise fall under "Inadequate Progress".', 'Accord high priority to the growth of manufacturing, so that we can create enough jobs in the country', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'accord-high-priority-to-the-growth-of-manufacturing-so-that-we-can-create-enough-jobs-in-the-country', '', '', '2017-05-27 18:09:54', '2017-05-27 12:39:54', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=494', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
(495, 3, '2017-05-17 16:58:41', '2017-05-17 11:28:41', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">India''s Gross National Savings (as percentage of GDP) continues to decrease from 33% in 2014 to 30% in 2016, reported by </span><a href="https://www.quandl.com/data/ODA/IND_NGSD_NGDP-India-Gross-National-Savings-of-GDP"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Quandl</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. However, there is an </span><a href="http://www.tradingeconomics.com/india/personal-savings"><span style="font-weight: 400;">improvement</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in the Indian Households Savings from Rs. 22.8 lakh crore in 2014 to Rs. 26.1 lakh crore in 2016. </span>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Government continued “</span><a href="https://pmjdy.gov.in/about"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pradhan Mantri jan Dhan Yojana</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">” to have better access &amp; boost savings of Individuals.  A total of 64,400 Crores have been </span><a href="http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/banking/finance/banking/deposits-in-jan-dhan-accounts-rise-to-rs-64250-crore/articleshow/55619794.cms"><span style="font-weight: 400;">deposited</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> as of May 2017.</span>', 'Encourage Savings as an important driver of investment and growth', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'encourage-savings-as-an-important-driver-of-investment-and-growth', '', '', '2017-05-19 11:48:05', '2017-05-19 06:18:05', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=495', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
(496, 3, '2017-05-17 16:58:07', '2017-05-17 11:28:07', 'The BJP government launched <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=155999">“Uchchtar Avishkaar Yojana”</a> in 2016 to promote industry-academia relationships. The project is currently been piloted in IITs. 92 projects have been approved till Jan 2017. A <a href="http://mhrd.gov.in/sites/upload_files/mhrd/files/ru2388.pdf">Council for Industry &amp; Higher Education Collaboration (CIHEC)</a> was also constituted with representatives from both academia and industry.\r\nThe <a href="http://www.aicte-india.org/downloads/Startup%20Policy.pdf">Start-Up Policy</a> formulated by the All India Council for Technical Education promotes student driven start ups by various measure including industry-academia interaction.', 'Institute a mechanism for interaction between industry (including SME), academia & community', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '486-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-17 16:58:07', '2017-05-17 11:28:07', '', 486, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/486-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
