(507, 3, '2017-05-17 17:02:54', '2017-05-17 11:32:54', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">There was an </span><a href="http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/economy/foreign-trade/india-leads-fdi-in-south-asia-with-34-billion-investment-in-2014-report/articleshow/47806243.cms"><span style="font-weight: 400;">abnormal decrease</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> (in outward FDI investment in India) in 2013 because of macro-economic uncertainties when some of the Indian MNCs divested. But, now it is back on track.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> India outward investment (OFDI) </span><a href="http://www.newindianexpress.com/business/2017/jan/27/indias-investment-abroad-soars-but-still-behind-china-1563900.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">rose by 32%</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in 2016 as compared to 2015.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">RBI </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">has </span><a href="https://www.ibef.org/economy/indian-investments-abroad"><span style="font-weight: 400;">relaxed the norms</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> for domestic companies investing abroad by doing away with the ceiling for raising funds through pledge of shares, domestic and overseas assets. It </span><a href="http://www.entrepreneurscouncil.in/Indian-Investments-Abroad.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">raised the annual overseas investment</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> ceiling to US$ 125,000 from US$ 75,000 to establish joint ventures (JV) and wholly owned subsidiaries.</span>\r\n\r\nThere has been a significant improvement in outward FDI. Hence,  it has been given the status "Adequate Progress".', 'Encourage Indian companies to go global and  support Indian companies in this endeavor', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'encourage-indian-companies-to-go-global-and-support-indian-companies-in-this-endeavor', '', '', '2017-05-27 18:18:51', '2017-05-27 12:48:51', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=507', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
