(538, 3, '2017-05-17 17:16:25', '2017-05-17 11:46:25', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government </span><a href="http://dipp.nic.in/English/Schemes/IIUS/IIUS_modified_01August2013.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">continued</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Modified Industrial Infrastructure Upgradation Scheme (MIIUS) under 12th year plan. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Under this Scheme, projects have been </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=156108"><span style="font-weight: 400;">undertaken to upgrade</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> infrastructure in existing Industrial Parks/ Estates/ Areas. This scheme was </span><a href="http://dipp.nic.in/English/Schemes/IIUS/IIUS_modified_01August2013.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">allocated</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Rs. 1030 crores &amp; the Central assistance of Rs. 513 crores has been </span><a href="http://dipp.nic.in/English/Schemes/IIUS/Progress_2017_18April2017.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">approved</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> under 12th year plan as of March, 2017 as </span><a href="http://dipp.nic.in/English/Schemes/IIUS/Progress_2017_18April2017.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">compared</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to allocated Rs. 1050 crores &amp; the central assistance of Rs. 378 crores under 11th year plan.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government </span><a href="http://www.financialexpress.com/budget/union-budget-2017-infrastructure-status-for-affordable-housing-to-boost-volume-of-construction-activities-experts/532352/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">launched</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">  “Housing for all by 2022” scheme under  Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (PMAY) </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">to boost affordable housing &amp; creating job potential through it.  While the target has been to construct 2 crore houses by 2022, a total of </span><a href="http://mhupa.gov.in/writereaddata/PMAY_Progress.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">6716 houses</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> have been built as of December, 2016.</span>\r\n\r\nSince there hasn''t been a sufficient increase in budget allocation &amp; in terms of providing houses, government has not done well. Hence, the progress has been classified as inadequate.', 'Harness the opportunities provided by the upgradation of infrastructure and housing, for its job generating potential', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'harness-the-opportunities-provided-by-the-upgradation-of-infrastructure-and-housing-for-its-job-generating-potential', '', '', '2017-05-28 00:32:04', '2017-05-27 19:02:04', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=538', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
