(601, 7, '2017-05-18 08:14:12', '2017-05-18 02:44:12', 'There is little clarity on the intent of this promise. <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=137143">National Medicinal Plants Board (NMPB) was setup in 2000</a><u>,</u> which is governed by Ministry of Ayurveda, Yoga and Naturopathy, Unani, Siddha and Homoeopathy (AYUSH). No effort has been taken for re-orienting the board.\r\n\r\nThe two schemes which encourage the farming of herbal plants are –\r\n\r\n1.Central Sector Scheme for Conservation, Development and Sustainable Management of Medicinal Plants under NMPB\r\n<ol start="2">\r\n 	<li><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/mbErel.aspx?relid=148832">Centrally Sponsored Scheme of National AYUSH Mission (NAM) has a component on “Medicinal Plants</a>”. Farming of medicinal plants was supported under the Centrally Sponsored Scheme of “National Mission on Medicinal Plants” of NMPB from 2009-2015, before NAM started.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThe budget allocated to the schemes has remained stagnant at <a href="http://ayush.gov.in/sites/default/files/AYUSH%20ENGLISH%20ANNUAL%20REPORT-2014-15_0.pdf">Rs 70 crores between 2014-15</a> and <a href="http://ayush.gov.in/sites/default/files/ANNUAL%20R%20EPORT%202016-17%20ENGLISH.pdf">2016-17</a>. A virtual market place, e-charak, was launched in August, 2016 to create trade linkages between buyers and sellers of medicinal plants.', 'Re-orientation of herbal plants board to encourage farming of herbal plants', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 're-orientation-of-herbal-plants-board-to-encourage-farming-of-herbal-plants', '', '', '2017-05-19 14:35:34', '2017-05-19 09:05:34', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=601', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
