(621, 7, '2017-05-18 08:35:34', '2017-05-18 03:05:34', 'India’s malnutrition statistics present an alarming picture, where more than <a href="http://rchiips.org/NFHS/pdf/NFHS4/India.pdf">35% children are underweight</a> and <a href="http://businessworld.in/article/World-Health-Day-India-s-Health-Report-Is-Unhealthy-/07-04-2017-115929/">70% of children between the age group of six months to three years suffer from anaemia</a>.\r\n\r\nBudgetary allocation for Integrated Child Development Scheme (ICDS) has declined from <a href="http://www.downtoearth.org.in/blog/union-budget-2015-children-left-asking-for-their-dues-as-ever-48885">Rs 18,200 crore in 2014-15</a> to <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=157886">Rs 16,800 crore in 2017-18</a>. The number of Special Newborn Care Units have seen marginal improvement, from <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/mbErel.aspx?relid=133548">525 in 2013-14 to 602 in Dec, 2015</a>.\r\n\r\nMission Indradhanush, a programme for universal immunisation of children has resulted in <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=155854">increase of full immunisation coverage by about 5-7%.</a> Overall, less budgetary allocation has impacted most of the child health programmes.', 'Move to pre-emptive care model where the focus and thrust will be on child health and prevention', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'move-to-pre-emptive-care-model-where-the-focus-and-thrust-will-be-on-child-health-and-prevention', '', '', '2017-05-19 13:55:31', '2017-05-19 08:25:31', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=621', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
