(666, 3, '2017-05-18 12:31:49', '2017-05-18 07:01:49', 'BJP government <a href="http://www.enam.gov.in/NAM/home/mandis.html#">launched e-NAM</a> (National Agriculture Market) in April, 2016 which is an electronic trading portal which networks the existing APMC mandis to create a unified national market for agricultural commodities. So far, 250 <a href="http://www.enam.gov.in/NAM/home/mandis.html#">Mandis</a> have been enrolled in it.\r\n\r\nCredit to Agriculture &amp; allied activities is <a href="http://www.business-standard.com/article/economy-policy/credit-to-industry-shrinks-1-9-in-mar-17-117042900055_1.html">increased</a> by 12.4 % in March, 2017 as compared to an increase of 15.3 % in March, 2015.\r\n\r\nParliament has <a href="http://www.prsindia.org/parliamenttrack/report-summaries/model-agricultural-land-leasing-act-2016-4270/">passed</a> Model Agricultural Land Leasing Act, 2016  to permit and facilitate leasing of agricultural land to farmers. It also provides for recognition of farmers cultivating on leased land to enable them to access loans through institutional credit.\r\n\r\nThe <a href="http://agricoop.nic.in/sites/default/files/APLM_ACT_LATEST_0.pdf">Model Agricultural Produce and Livestock Marketing </a>(APLM) act, 2017 allows farmers to sell their produce directly to the private sector players. However, no state has implemented the act to date.', 'Strengthen the traditional employment bases of agriculture and allied industries, and retail - through modernization as well as stronger credit and market linkages', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'promise-strengthen-the-traditional-employment-bases-of-agriculture-and-allied-industries-and-retail-through-modernization-as-well-as-stronger-credit-and-market-linkages', '', '', '2017-05-19 15:07:59', '2017-05-19 09:37:59', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=666', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
(668, 3, '2017-05-18 12:31:49', '2017-05-18 07:01:49', 'BJP government <a href="http://www.enam.gov.in/NAM/home/mandis.html#">launched e-NAM</a> (National Agriculture Market) in April, 2016 which is an electronic trading portal which networks the existing APMC mandis to create a unified national market for agricultural commodities. So far, 250 <a href="http://www.enam.gov.in/NAM/home/mandis.html#">Mandis</a> have been enrolled in it.\r\n\r\nCredit to Agriculture &amp; allied activities is <a href="http://www.business-standard.com/article/economy-policy/credit-to-industry-shrinks-1-9-in-mar-17-117042900055_1.html">increased</a> by 12.4 % in March, 2017 as compared to an increase of 15.3 % in March, 2015.\r\n\r\nParliament has <a href="http://www.prsindia.org/parliamenttrack/report-summaries/model-agricultural-land-leasing-act-2016-4270/">passed</a> Model Agricultural Land Leasing Act, 2016  to permit and facilitate leasing of agricultural land to farmers. It also provides for recognition of farmers cultivating on leased land to enable them to access loans through institutional credit.\r\n\r\nThe <a href="http://agricoop.nic.in/sites/default/files/APLM_ACT_LATEST_0.pdf">Model Agricultural Produce and Livestock Marketing </a>(APLM) act, 2017 allows farmers to sell their produce directly to the private sector players. However, no state has implemented the act to date.', 'Promise: Strengthen the traditional employment bases of agriculture and allied industries, and retail - through modernization as well as stronger credit and market linkages', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '666-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-18 12:31:49', '2017-05-18 07:01:49', '', 666, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/666-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(671, 3, '2017-05-18 12:37:30', '2017-05-18 07:07:30', '<a href="http://midh.gov.in/">Mission for Integrated Development of Horticulture (MIDH)</a> was launched by the UPA government to integrate all the schemes on horticulture. National Mission on Horticulture, launched under UPA, has been allocated <a href="http://164.100.47.193/lsscommittee/Agriculture/16_Agriculture_35.pdf">Rs. 2300 crores in 2017-18</a>, up from Rs. 1600 crores in 2016-17. However, no data of beneficiaries is available.\r\n\r\nUnder MIDH, <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/erelcontent.aspx?relid=113416">financial assistance</a> is also provided for Beekeeping for pollination and <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=158201">Floriculture</a>. The BJP government increased the FDI limit for Pisciculture, Aquaculture, Apiculture to <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=149381">100% in 2016</a>.\r\n\r\nHowever, the horticulture production of the country rose marginally by 0.3% from <a href="http://164.100.47.190/loksabhaquestions/annex/11/AU3216.pdf">286 million tonnes in 2015-16 to 287 million tonnes in 2016-17</a>.', 'Promote horticulture, floriculture, pisciculture, bee-keeping and poultry for generating jobs and income for rural India', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'promote-horticulture-floriculture-pisciculture-bee-keeping-and-poultry-for-generating-jobs-and-income-for-rural-india', '', '', '2017-05-23 19:24:39', '2017-05-23 13:54:39', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=671', 0, 'promise', '', 1),
(672, 3, '2017-05-18 12:37:30', '2017-05-18 07:07:30', '<a href="http://midh.gov.in/">Mission for Integrated Development of Horticulture (MIDH)</a> was launched by the UPA government to integrate all the schemes on horticulture. The BJP government has increased allocation for MIDH from Rs. 2300 crore in 2017-18. However, no data of beneficiaries is available.\r\n\r\nUnder MIDH, <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/erelcontent.aspx?relid=113416">financial assistance</a> is also provided for Beekeeping for pollination and <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=158201">Floriculture</a>. The BJP government increased the FDI limit for Pisciculture, Aquaculture, Apiculture to <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=149381">100% in 2016</a>.\r\n\r\nHowever, the horticulture production of the country rose marginally by 0.3% from <a href="http://164.100.47.190/loksabhaquestions/annex/11/AU3216.pdf">286 million tonnes in 2015-16 to 287 million tonnes in 2016-17</a>.', 'Promote horticulture, floriculture, pisciculture, bee-keeping and poultry for generating jobs and income for rural India', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '671-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-18 12:37:30', '2017-05-18 07:07:30', '', 671, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/671-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(673, 3, '2017-05-19 12:17:02', '2017-05-19 06:47:02', 'The BJP government launched a television channel dedicated to Farmers (<a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=122039">DD Kisan</a>) in May 2015. Viewership of the channel is around <a href="http://www.indiantelevision.com/television/tv-channels/terrestrial/dd-kisan-viewership-is-72m-a-month-received-rs-800m-govt-funds-for-17-18-170408">73 lakh per month</a> on average. Funds allocated for the channel has increased from<a href="http://www.indiantelevision.com/television/tv-channels/terrestrial/dd-kisan-viewership-is-72m-a-month-received-rs-800m-govt-funds-for-17-18-170408"> Rs. 26 crores in 2014-15 to Rs. 70 crores in 2016-17</a>. The programmes are <a href="http://164.100.47.190/loksabhaquestions/annex/10/AS390.pdf">translated into regional languages</a> by other Doordarshan Kendras.\n\nHowever, no regional Kisan TV channels have been set up. Hence, region specific information is not delivered to farmers in real time.', 'Explore setting up of regional Kisan TV channels', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '562-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 12:17:02', '2017-05-19 06:47:02', '', 562, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/562-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
