(678, 3, '2017-05-18 12:57:24', '2017-05-18 07:27:24', 'BJP Government has not launched any fresh National Litigation Policy or amended <a href="https://www.google.co.in/url?sa=t&amp;rct=j&amp;q=&amp;esrc=s&amp;source=web&amp;cd=3&amp;cad=rja&amp;uact=8&amp;ved=0ahUKEwi1286j2KjTAhUEw7wKHY8uCsEQFgg2MAI&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.lawmin.nic.in%2Fla%2Fnlp.doc&amp;usg=AFQjCNHs-s6uBfBIPYnj3biLurwu4xBXug&amp;sig2=pV8Ry8S6Izmq6p90-VjnSA">National Litigation Policy, 2010.</a> This is important since nearly half of the litigation in Indian courts involve governments in one way or the other furthering adding to the judicial backlog. An undated <a href="http://lawmin.nic.in/la/status%20note%20on%20nlp.pdf">note from Ministry of law</a> claims that the National Litigation Policy is under consideration.\r\n\r\nHowever, BJP government has not launched any fresh National Litigation Policy or amended it and therefore the performance against this promise has been classified as "Yet to Start"\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Implement the National Litigation Policy in letter and spirit to reduce average pendency time of cases', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'implement-the-national-litigation-policy-in-letter-and-spirit-to-reduce-average-pendency-time-of-cases', '', '', '2017-05-19 12:42:32', '2017-05-19 07:12:32', '', 0, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/?post_type=promise&#038;p=678', 0, 'promise', '', 0),
