(694, 4, '2017-06-02 19:42:09', '2017-06-02 14:12:09', '<img class="wp-image-345 aligncenter" src="http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/1.jpg" alt="" width="269" height="341" />\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<p style="text-align: center;">On 16th May 2014, Bhartiya Janta Party (BJP) won the electoral vote and Narendra Modi took oath as 14th Prime Minister of India on 26th May 2014. Election Promises Tracker is a citizen initiative that tracks governments'' performance against the promises the party made to the electorate in the fields of Education, Health, Governance, Economy, Industries, and Agriculture. The promises have, primarily,  been taken from BJP''s Lok Sabha 2014 Elections Manifesto which can be accessed <a href="http://www.bjp.org/images/pdf_2014/full_manifesto_english_07.04.2014.pdf">here</a>. Please read our guidelines for categorization of promises <a href="http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/categorization-guidelines/">here</a>. Write to anuragkundu@electionpromisestracker.in in case you observe any discrepancy</p>', 'Central-Government', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '356-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-06-02 19:42:09', '2017-06-02 14:12:09', '', 356, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/356-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
