(883, 3, '2017-05-18 23:22:09', '2017-05-18 17:52:09', 'There is no evidence that establishes any efforts on the part of Government of India to fulfill this promise. Several BJP politicians have issued statements reiterating their stand, however nothing has been initiated by the government.', 'Explore all possibilities within the framework of the constitution to facilitate the construction of the Ram Temple in Ayodhya', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '708-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-18 23:22:09', '2017-05-18 17:52:09', '', 708, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/708-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(884, 4, '2017-05-18 23:24:37', '2017-05-18 17:54:37', '<a href="http://midh.gov.in/">Mission for Integrated Development of Horticulture (MIDH)</a> was launched by the UPA government to integrate all the schemes on horticulture. National Mission on Horticulture has been allocated <a href="http://164.100.47.193/lsscommittee/Agriculture/16_Agriculture_35.pdf">Rs. 2300 crores in 2017-18</a>, up from Rs. 1600 crores in 2016-17. . However, no data of beneficiaries is available.\n\nUnder MIDH, <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/erelcontent.aspx?relid=113416">financial assistance</a> is also provided for Beekeeping for pollination and <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=158201">Floriculture</a>. The BJP government increased the FDI limit for Pisciculture, Aquaculture, Apiculture to <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=149381">100% in 2016</a>.\n\nHowever, the horticulture production of the country rose marginally by 0.3% from <a href="http://164.100.47.190/loksabhaquestions/annex/11/AU3216.pdf">286 million tonnes in 2015-16 to 287 million tonnes in 2016-17</a>.', 'Promote horticulture, floriculture, pisciculture, bee-keeping and poultry for generating jobs and income for rural India', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '671-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-18 23:24:37', '2017-05-18 17:54:37', '', 671, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/671-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(885, 3, '2017-05-18 23:25:45', '2017-05-18 17:55:45', 'Supreme Court in <a href="http://www.supremecourtcases.com/index2.php?option=com_content&amp;itemid=135&amp;do_pdf=1&amp;id=21218">Prakash Singh Vs. Union of India </a>case <a href="http://www.humanrightsinitiative.org/programs/aj/police/india/initiatives/seven_steps_to_police_reform.pdf">recommended </a>seven steps for making Police more fair, transparent, citizen-friendly and free from political interference.  The promiment recommendations include security of tenure for Police officers, separation of investigation functions of police from law and order, setting up of Police Complaint Authority to inquire into the complaints against the police offers, Model Police Bill hasn’t been tabled by BJP government.', 'Strengthen Police for investigations, making them Swift, Transparent, Fair, Clear and Decisive - acting as an inescapable deterrent to wrongdoers and a protective shield to the innocent', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '706-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-18 23:25:45', '2017-05-18 17:55:45', '', 706, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/706-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(886, 4, '2017-05-18 23:25:10', '2017-05-18 17:55:10', '<a href="http://midh.gov.in/">Mission for Integrated Development of Horticulture (MIDH)</a> was launched by the UPA government to integrate all the schemes on horticulture. National Mission on Horticulture, launched under has been allocated <a href="http://164.100.47.193/lsscommittee/Agriculture/16_Agriculture_35.pdf">Rs. 2300 crores in 2017-18</a>, up from Rs. 1600 crores in 2016-17. However, no data of beneficiaries is available.\r\n\r\nUnder MIDH, <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/erelcontent.aspx?relid=113416">financial assistance</a> is also provided for Beekeeping for pollination and <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=158201">Floriculture</a>. The BJP government increased the FDI limit for Pisciculture, Aquaculture, Apiculture to <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=149381">100% in 2016</a>.\r\n\r\nHowever, the horticulture production of the country rose marginally by 0.3% from <a href="http://164.100.47.190/loksabhaquestions/annex/11/AU3216.pdf">286 million tonnes in 2015-16 to 287 million tonnes in 2016-17</a>.', 'Promote horticulture, floriculture, pisciculture, bee-keeping and poultry for generating jobs and income for rural India', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '671-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-18 23:25:10', '2017-05-18 17:55:10', '', 671, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/671-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(887, 3, '2017-05-18 23:26:46', '2017-05-18 17:56:46', 'Supreme Court in <a href="http://www.supremecourtcases.com/index2.php?option=com_content&amp;itemid=135&amp;do_pdf=1&amp;id=21218">Prakash Singh Vs. Union of India </a>case <a href="http://www.humanrightsinitiative.org/programs/aj/police/india/initiatives/seven_steps_to_police_reform.pdf">recommended </a>seven steps for making Police more fair, transparent, citizen-friendly and free from political interference.  The prominent recommendations include security of tenure for Police officers, separation of investigation functions of police from law and order, setting up of Police Complaint Authority to inquire into the complaints against the police offers, and setting up of Police Establishment Board to decide matters of transfers, postings and promotions. However, Model Police Bill hasn’t been tabled by BJP government.', 'Strengthen Police for investigations, making them Swift, Transparent, Fair, Clear and Decisive - acting as an inescapable deterrent to wrongdoers and a protective shield to the innocent', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '706-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-18 23:26:46', '2017-05-18 17:56:46', '', 706, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/706-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
