(898, 3, '2017-05-18 23:49:26', '2017-05-18 18:19:26', 'No government order has been issued to create separate courts for handling Intellectual Property Rights (IPR) Cases. However, the National Intellectual Property Rights Policy 2016 proposes to<a href="http://dipp.nic.in/English/Schemes/Intellectual_Property_Rights/National_IPR_Policy_08.08.2016.pdf"> adjudicate IP disputes through commercial courts</a> under the Commercial Courts Act 2015.\n\nIt is not only the text but the spirit and context that matter, the promise has been fulfilled in spirit, the performance against this promise has been classified as "Fulfilled".', 'Create courts specially equipped to deal with IPR cases', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '680-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-18 23:49:26', '2017-05-18 18:19:26', '', 680, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/680-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(899, 3, '2017-05-18 23:50:00', '2017-05-18 18:20:00', 'No government order has been issued to create separate courts for handling Intellectual Property Rights (IPR) Cases. However, the National Intellectual Property Rights Policy 2016 proposes to<a href="http://dipp.nic.in/English/Schemes/Intellectual_Property_Rights/National_IPR_Policy_08.08.2016.pdf"> adjudicate IP disputes through commercial courts</a> under the Commercial Courts Act 2015.\r\n\r\nIt is not only the text but the spirit and context that matter too and therefore the performance against this promise has been classified as "Fulfilled" since the promise has been realised in spirit.', 'Create courts specially equipped to deal with IPR cases', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '680-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-18 23:50:00', '2017-05-18 18:20:00', '', 680, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/680-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(900, 3, '2017-05-18 23:53:26', '2017-05-18 18:23:26', 'BJP Government has not launched any fresh National Litigation Policy or amended <a href="https://www.google.co.in/url?sa=t&amp;rct=j&amp;q=&amp;esrc=s&amp;source=web&amp;cd=3&amp;cad=rja&amp;uact=8&amp;ved=0ahUKEwi1286j2KjTAhUEw7wKHY8uCsEQFgg2MAI&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.lawmin.nic.in%2Fla%2Fnlp.doc&amp;usg=AFQjCNHs-s6uBfBIPYnj3biLurwu4xBXug&amp;sig2=pV8Ry8S6Izmq6p90-VjnSA">National Litigation Policy, 2010.</a> This is important since nearly half of the litigation in Indian courts involve governments in one way or the other furthering adding to the judicial backlog. However, BJP government has not launched any fresh National Litigation Policy or amended it though an undated <a href="http://lawmin.nic.in/la/status%20note%20on%20nlp.pdf">note from Ministry of law</a> claims that it is under consideration.', 'Implement the National Litigation Policy in letter and spirit to reduce average pendency time of cases', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '678-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-18 23:53:26', '2017-05-18 18:23:26', '', 678, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/678-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
