are Engineer at Paytm.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_team_member][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_3"][et_pb_team_member admin_label="Team Member" name="Sajal Singh" position="Fact Checker" image_url="http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/18157323_10210986115722890_128516437352806744_n-165x190.jpg" animation="fade_in" background_layout="light" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"]\r\n\r\nSajal is a politics enthusiast. A post graduate in Economics, he loves to debate and discuss politically incorrect issues and believes that nothing should be taboo in a mature democracy. He has been associated with a number of education start ups the most prominent being civilsdaily.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_team_member][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_3"][et_pb_team_member admin_label="Team Member" name="Vidur Khanna" position="Technology" image_url="http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/13592756_1019941838102778_7998836317871435894_n-198x198.jpg" animation="fade_in" background_layout="light" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"]\r\n\r\nVidur graduated from NIT Kurukshetra and currently works with PayTM.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_team_member][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row admin_label="row"][et_pb_column type="1_3"][et_pb_team_member admin_label="Team Member" name="Shriram" position="Intern" image_url="http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/11905774_932163730231454_9106338492012823653_n-250x160.jpg" animation="fade_in" background_layout="light" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"]\r\n\r\nShriram is a graduate in Chemistry from St. Stephen''s College, Delhi.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_team_member][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_3"][et_pb_team_member admin_label="Team Member" name="Munish Kaushik" position="Metor" image_url="http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/pp-250x250.jpg" animation="fade_in" background_layout="light" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"]\r\n\r\nMunish is a development professional with a child-like heart. He has 16 years of experience of working for Child Rights and Disaster Management. He works with Delhi Government in education and participatory governance related projects. He has a really cool website. Do check out: http://www.munshiinpublicservice.com\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_team_member][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_3"][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section]', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '789-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 01:05:59', '2017-05-18 19:35:59', '', 789, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/789-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(938, 3, '2017-05-19 01:08:17', '2017-05-18 19:38:17', 'No such commission has been set up by the BJP government. A <a href="http://mhrd.gov.in/sites/upload_files/mhrd/files/nep/press-releases.pdf">Drafting Committee</a> was set up to prepare a <a href="http://nuepa.org/NEW/download/NEP2016/ReportNEP.pdf">draft NEP</a>, however, the policy hasn’t been accepted by the BJP government. <a href="http://www.livemint.com/Education/D1P0mMtV13lMa86gJjbA9H/Govt-to-announce-new-panel-for-drafting-National-Education-P.html">No new committee</a> has been set up by the government to prepare a new draft for NEP.\n\nSince the new committee', 'Set up a National Commission on Education to recommend New Education Policy (NEP)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '542-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 01:08:17', '2017-05-18 19:38:17', '', 542, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/542-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(939, 3, '2017-05-19 01:08:43', '2017-05-18 19:38:43', 'No such commission has been set up by the BJP government. A <a href="http://mhrd.gov.in/sites/upload_files/mhrd/files/nep/press-releases.pdf">Drafting Committee</a> was set up to prepare a <a href="http://nuepa.org/NEW/download/NEP2016/ReportNEP.pdf">draft NEP</a>, however, the policy hasn’t been accepted by the BJP government. <a href="http://www.livemint.com/Education/D1P0mMtV13lMa86gJjbA9H/Govt-to-announce-new-panel-for-drafting-National-Education-P.html">No new committee</a> has been set up by the government to prepare a new draft for NEP.\r\n\r\nSince the new committee is yet to be set up, the performance against this promise has been classified as "Yet to Start"', 'Set up a National Commission on Education to recommend New Education Policy (NEP)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '542-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 01:08:43', '2017-05-18 19:38:43', '', 542, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/542-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(940, 3, '2017-05-19 01:12:31', '2017-05-18 19:42:31', 'The <a href="http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/parliament-passes-apprentices-bill/article6637197.ece">Apprenticeship Act was amended</a> and then notified in December 2014. The amendments were aimed at enhancing the skills of youth and make them employable.  Some amendments that facilitate Apprenticeship includes mandating a certain percentage of the workforce to be hired as apprentices, and increasing the minimum age for apprentices in hazardous industries. Though the promise has been fulfilled by the BJP government, two provisions, however, deserve to be explicitly called out for they seek to undermine the rights and dignity of the apprentices. The Act removes imprisonment as punishment for violating the provisions of the Apprentices Act. This makes the Act open to misuse. The Act further allows employers full liberty to fix work hours, and leaves of the apprentices as per their discretion. Both the clauses become quite dangerous in their application in a setting where profit is the guiding principle.\n\nSince the', 'Revisit the Apprenticeship Act to facilitate our youth to Earn while they Learn', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '531-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 01:12:31', '2017-05-18 19:42:31', '', 531, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/531-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(941, 3, '2017-05-19 01:12:35', '2017-05-18 19:42:35', 'The <a href="http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/parliament-passes-apprentices-bill/article6637197.ece">Apprenticeship Act was amended</a> and then notified in December 2014. The amendments were aimed at enhancing the skills of youth and make them employable.  Some amendments that facilitate Apprenticeship includes mandating a certain percentage of the workforce to be hired as apprentices, and increasing the minimum age for apprentices in hazardous industries. Though the promise has been fulfilled by the BJP government, two provisions, however, deserve to be explicitly called out for they seek to undermine the rights and dignity of the apprentices. The Act removes imprisonment as punishment for violating the provisions of the Apprentices Act. This makes the Act open to misuse. The Act further allows employers full liberty to fix work hours, and leaves of the apprentices as per their discretion. Both the clauses become quite dangerous in their application in a setting where profit is the guiding principle.', 'Revisit the Apprenticeship Act to facilitate our youth to Earn while they Learn', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '531-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 01:12:35', '2017-05-18 19:42:35', '', 531, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/531-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
