(972, 3, '2017-05-19 14:54:59', '2017-05-19 09:24:59', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">The BJP government did not set up any Task Force to tackle black money. However, in compliance with a Supreme Court directive, it constituted a Supreme Court monitored </span><a href="http://www.aljazeera.com/news/asia/2014/05/india-sets-up-team-unearth-black-money-201452895658124791.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Special Investigation Team</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> (SIT) on Black Money.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Till March 2017,the SIT had detected black money worth </span><a href="http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/70k-crore-in-black-money-detected-scappointed-sit/article17397208.ece"><span style="font-weight: 400;">₹70,000 crore</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, which included ₹16,000 crore stashed abroad.</span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">On its recommendation, the BJP government declared cash transactions </span><a href="http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/cash-transaction-limit-slashed-to-rs-2-lakh/article17561911.ece"><span style="font-weight: 400;">above Rs. 2 lakh</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> as illegal. The BJP government however did not accept SIT’s recommendation on</span><a href="https://ilt.taxmann.com/topstories/222330000000008196/cash-transactions-above-rs-3-lakhs-to-be-declared-illegal-and-punishable-sit-on-black-money.aspx"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> limiting cash holding to Rs. 15 lakh</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The</span><a href="http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/10-things-to-know-about-blackmoney-bill/article7194290.ece"> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Undisclosed Foreign Income and Assets (Imposition of Tax) Bill, 2015</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> was enacted, which introduced stringent penalties and enhanced punishment for those with undisclosed income or wealth abroad. It came into effect from July 1, 2015</span>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Benami Transactions (Prohibition) Act was amended and came into </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=159882"><span style="font-weight: 400;">force on November 1, 2016</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">An interdepartmental </span><a href="http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/Govt.-sets-up-inter-departmental-task-force-to-crack-down-on-benami-firms/article17286171.ece"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Task Force</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> for a crack-down on Benami transactions was set-up.</span>', 'Set up a Task Force to tackle black money and to recommend amendments to existing laws or enact new laws', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '473-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 14:54:59', '2017-05-19 09:24:59', '', 473, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/473-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(973, 3, '2017-05-19 15:12:03', '2017-05-19 09:42:03', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">The BJP government has</span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=116587"> <span style="font-weight: 400;">approved</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> setting up of “</span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Technology Centre Systems program</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;">” for MSMEs under which 15 new Technology Development Centers are proposed to be established, and the existing centers are proposed to be upgraded over next six years. The objective of thee centres is to provide support to Electronics Systems Design &amp; Manufacturing.  Construction for 4 such technology centers has been </span><a href="http://msme.gov.in/sites/default/files/Achievments_Brochure_Final__17-05-16_.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">started</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> so far.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government </span><a href="http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/budget-2015/student/Union-Budget-2015-Rs-150-crore-alloted-for-research-under-Atal-Innovation-Mission/articleshow/46413665.cms"><span style="font-weight: 400;">launched</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Atal Innovation Mission (AIM) in Budget 2015 with an allocation of Rs. 150 crores out of which only </span><a href="http://164.100.47.193/lsscommittee/Finance/16_Finance_48.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Rs. 16.8 crores have been used</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. In Budget 2017-18, allocation for this scheme has been </span><a href="http://164.100.47.193/lsscommittee/Finance/16_Finance_48.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">reduced</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to Rs. 112 crores.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">To promote innovation in MSMEs, 21 out of 80 </span><a href="http://www.pib.nic.in/newsite/mbErel.aspx?relid=133167"><span style="font-weight: 400;">promised</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> livelihood business incubators have been </span><a href="http://msme.gov.in/sites/default/files/Achievments_Brochure_Final__17-05-16_.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">approved</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> under the scheme ASPIRE launched in March, 2015. One such incubator has been set up in Deoria, U.P in April, 2015. Another incubators in Rajkot &amp; </span><a href="http://knnindia.co.in/news/newsdetails/msme/kalraj-mishra-inaugurates-livelihood-business-incubation-at-jamia-under-aspire"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Jamia</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> have been inaugurated in Dec, 2015 &amp; Nov., 2016 respectively.</span>', 'Support in R&D and innovation in MSMEs', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '527-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 15:12:03', '2017-05-19 09:42:03', '', 527, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/527-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(974, 3, '2017-05-19 15:15:29', '2017-05-19 09:45:29', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">FIPB’s functioning was improved by developing an </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=115538"><span style="font-weight: 400;">upgraded and secure portal</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, for e-filings of FDI applications. It made the process of application simpler, transparent, easily accessible and paperless. </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The BJP government, in its budget 2017, proposed the </span><a href="http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/economy/policy/government-abolishes-fipb-more-fdi-policy-easing-on-anvil/articleshow/56909680.cms"><span style="font-weight: 400;">abolition of FIPB</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, as e-filing and online processing of FDI application had been successfully implemented and over 90% of FDi was coming into the country through the automatic route. </span>\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">FIPB was an inter-ministerial body that processed FDI proposals that came through the approval route and made recommendations to the government for approval.The BJP government is yet to announce the new system of approval for FDI applications.</span>', 'The Foreign Investment Promotion Board (FIPB) functioning shall be made more efficient and investor friendly', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '464-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 15:15:29', '2017-05-19 09:45:29', '', 464, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/464-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
