wever, on </span><a href="http://www.moneycontrol.com/news/trends/current-affairs-trends/sc-asks-govt-whether-sit-needed-to-probe-panama-papers-2260585.htmlhttp://www.moneycontrol.com/news/trends/current-affairs-trends/sc-asks-govt-whether-sit-needed-to-probe-panama-papers-2260585.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">18th Apri</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">l, the BJP government was required to submit all reports by the MAG so far, to the SC in sealed cover. The SC has asked the BJP government whether a SIT needs to be set-up to probe the off-shore accounts of Indians revealed in the Panama papers.</span>', 'To initiate the process of tracking down and bringing back black money stashed in foreign banks and offshore accounts', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '466-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 15:18:49', '2017-05-19 09:48:49', '', 466, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/466-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(978, 3, '2017-05-19 15:19:35', '2017-05-19 09:49:35', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government </span><a href="http://www.financialexpress.com/economy/employment-opportunities-to-1-crore-youth-by-2020-bandaru-dattatreya/517086/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">decided</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to transform 100 Employment Exchanges out of 978 existing centres into </span><a href="http://www.mcc-centre.com/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Model Career Centres</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> (MCC). </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Government </span><a href="http://www.business-standard.com/article/government-press-release/upgradation-of-employment-exchanges-117020800698_1.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">provides financial assistance</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to these centres upto Rs 50 lakh per centre based on the proposals and scheme guidelines. The Centre has already </span><a href="http://www.business-standard.com/article/economy-policy/coming-soon-model-career-centres-for-jobseekers-116012600013_1.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">allocated money</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to states for 70 such centres. The portal provides the data only for three such centres at Gurgaon, Mumbai and Chennai.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Ministry of Labour &amp; Employment launched National Career Center (NCS) </span><a href="https://www.ncs.gov.in/Pages/default.aspx"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Portal</span></a> <span style="font-weight: 400;">to transform the existing National Employment Service &amp; </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/printrelease.aspx?relid=161407"><span style="font-weight: 400;">linking all employment exchanges</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> of the country. The Centre partly funded the IT upgradation for this initiative.</span>', 'Transform our Employment Exchanges into Career Centres - connecting our youth with job opportunities in a transparent and effective manner through the use of technology; as well as providing counselling and training', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '544-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 15:19:35', '2017-05-19 09:49:35', '', 544, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/544-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(979, 3, '2017-05-19 15:22:25', '2017-05-19 09:52:25', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">On 13th May 2016, the cabinet approved the </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=145338"><span style="font-weight: 400;">National Intellectual Property Rights (IPR) Policy</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. It is a vision statement which aims to create synergies across different components in the IPR sector. While the IPR policy is balanced, but real progress will depend on whether it is supported by legislative reforms or not. </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The BJP government also revised the Start-Up Intellectual Property Protection </span><a href="http://ipspectra.ztmbpd.iari.res.in/Acts%20and%20Ruels/Policy/SIPP%20Scheme.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">(SIPP)</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> scheme and made</span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=123202"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> patent filing</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> process online, cost effective and transparent.  Patent filings </span><a href="http://www.ipindia.nic.in/writereaddata/Portal/IPOAnnualReport/1_71_1_Annual_Report_2015-16_English__2_.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">increased by 10%</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in the fiscal 2015-16.</span>\n\n<a href="http://www.livemint.com/Politics/jEaTS5ZzyoyTBXNWWXHSbP/Over-1-lakh-patents-filed-since-2013.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Indian patent data</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> shows that a massive 73% of the patents here are filed by foreigners and foreign entities, and only 27% ,by Indians/ Indian entities. </span>', 'Will embark on the path of IPRs and Patents in a big way', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '427-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 15:22:25', '2017-05-19 09:52:25', '', 427, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/427-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(980, 3, '2017-05-19 15:24:42', '2017-05-19 09:54:42', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">On 13th May 2016, the cabinet approved the </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=145338"><span style="font-weight: 400;">National Intellectual Property Rights (IPR) Policy</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. It is a vision statement which aims to create synergies across different components in the IPR sector. While the IPR policy is balanced, but real progress will depend on whether it is supported by legislative reforms or not. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The BJP government also revised the Start-Up Intellectual Property Protection </span><a href="http://ipspectra.ztmbpd.iari.res.in/Acts%20and%20Ruels/Policy/SIPP%20Scheme.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">(SIPP)</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> scheme and made</span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=123202"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> patent filing</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> process online, cost-effective and transparent.  Patent filings </span><a href="http://www.ipindia.nic.in/writereaddata/Portal/IPOAnnualReport/1_71_1_Annual_Report_2015-16_English__2_.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">increased by 10%</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in the fiscal 2015-16.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.livemint.com/Politics/jEaTS5ZzyoyTBXNWWXHSbP/Over-1-lakh-patents-filed-since-2013.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Indian patent data</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> shows that a massive 73% of the patents here are filed by foreigners and foreign entities, and only 27% ,by Indians/ Indian entities. </span>', 'Will embark on the path of IPRs and Patents in a big way', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '427-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 15:24:42', '2017-05-19 09:54:42', '', 427, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/427-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
