(984, 3, '2017-05-19 16:17:12', '2017-05-19 10:47:12', 'The BJP government revised the <a href="http://www.ugc.ac.in/pdfnews/0414893_Final-Prepare-XII-Plan-Guidelines-For-Website-.pdf">Guidelines for Autonomous Colleges</a> in April 2016. Now, the university has to decide on the application for autonomous status by affiliated colleges within <a href="http://www.hindustantimes.com/education/varsities-get-3-months-to-decide-on-autonomy-of-colleges/story-LqWo14mlHbZKxXZ29ABpGM.html">3 months</a>. In case, the university fails to reach a decision, it will be presumed that the university has no objection to granting the autonomous status. The number of autonomous colleges in India has gone up from <a href="http://www.myengg.com/engg/info/38413/state-wise-list-of-autonomous-colleges-in-india-approved-by-ugc/">487 in 2014</a> to <a href="http://164.100.47.194/Loksabha/Questions/QResult15.aspx?qref=49145&amp;lsno=16">595 in 2017</a>. This is an important measure taken by MHRD.\n\nThe <a href="http://www.prsindia.org/billtrack/the-indian-institutes-of-management-bill-2017-4607/">IIM Bill</a> 2017, pending in the Lok Sabha, proposes to provide IIMs with the power to appoint their own Directors and Chairpersons. The bill is designed to increase the autonomy of IIMs.\n\nThe performance has been clas\n\nIt deserves to be mentioned that multiple senior position holders in Indian Universities including <a href="https://blogs.wsj.com/indiarealtime/2015/02/22/in-full-amartya-sens-nalanda-university-resignation-letter/">Dr. Amartya Sen</a> and <a href="http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/nalanda-university-chancellor-george-yeo-resigns-from-post-cites-attack-on-autonomy-as-reason-4394182/">George Deo</a> (Both from Nalanda University), <a href="http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/education/news/IIT-Delhi-director-RK-Shevgaonkar-quits-over-demand-for-Subramanian-Swamys-dues/articleshow/45663599.cms">RK Shevgaonkar</a> (IIT Delhi) and <a href="http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-others/anil-kakodkar-rebuts-smriti-irani-i-am-out-of-the-process/">Anil Kakodkar</a> (IIT Bombay) have resigned since 2014 citing attack on autonomy and disagreements with the BJP government amid other reasons.', 'Provide autonomy with steps to ensure accountability for institutions of higher learning', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '503-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 16:17:12', '2017-05-19 10:47:12', '', 503, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/503-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(985, 3, '2017-05-19 16:17:58', '2017-05-19 10:47:58', 'The BJP government revised the <a href="http://www.ugc.ac.in/pdfnews/0414893_Final-Prepare-XII-Plan-Guidelines-For-Website-.pdf">Guidelines for Autonomous Colleges</a> in April 2016. Now, the university has to decide on the application for autonomous status by affiliated colleges within <a href="http://www.hindustantimes.com/education/varsities-get-3-months-to-decide-on-autonomy-of-colleges/story-LqWo14mlHbZKxXZ29ABpGM.html">3 months</a>. In case, the university fails to reach a decision, it will be presumed that the university has no objection to granting the autonomous status. The number of autonomous colleges in India has gone up from <a href="http://www.myengg.com/engg/info/38413/state-wise-list-of-autonomous-colleges-in-india-approved-by-ugc/">487 in 2014</a> to <a href="http://164.100.47.194/Loksabha/Questions/QResult15.aspx?qref=49145&amp;lsno=16">595 in 2017</a>. This is an important measure taken by MHRD.\r\n\r\nThe <a href="http://www.prsindia.org/billtrack/the-indian-institutes-of-management-bill-2017-4607/">IIM Bill</a> 2017, pending in the Lok Sabha, proposes to provide IIMs with the power to appoint their own Directors and Chairpersons. The bill is designed to increase the autonomy of IIMs.\r\n\r\nThe performance against this promise has been classified as "Adequate Progress" since the IIM Bill has only been tabled thus far and it remains to be seen whether Parliament passes the bill.\r\n\r\nHowever, it deserves to be mentioned that multiple senior position holders in Indian Universities including <a href="https://blogs.wsj.com/indiarealtime/2015/02/22/in-full-amartya-sens-nalanda-university-resignation-letter/">Dr. Amartya Sen</a> and <a href="http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/nalanda-university-chancellor-george-yeo-resigns-from-post-cites-attack-on-autonomy-as-reason-4394182/">George Deo</a> (Both from Nalanda University), <a href="http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/education/news/IIT-Delhi-director-RK-Shevgaonkar-quits-over-demand-for-Subramanian-Swamys-dues/articleshow/45663599.cms">RK Shevgaonkar</a> (IIT Delhi) and <a href="http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-others/anil-kakodkar-rebuts-smriti-irani-i-am-out-of-the-process/">Anil Kakodkar</a> (IIT Bombay) have resigned since 2014 citing attack on autonomy and disagreements with the BJP government amid other reasons.', 'Provide autonomy with steps to ensure accountability for institutions of higher learning', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '503-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 16:17:58', '2017-05-19 10:47:58', '', 503, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/503-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(986, 3, '2017-05-19 16:26:12', '2017-05-19 10:56:12', '<a href="https://www.topuniversities.com/university-rankings/world-university-rankings/2016">Two Indian Universities</a> feature in top 200 in the year 2016, according to the QS World University Ranking, as against <a href="https://www.topuniversities.com/university-rankings/world-university-rankings/2013">none in 2013</a>. The BJP government has launched programs such as IMPRINT India, Uchhatar Avishkar Yojana (UAY) and Global Initiative of Academic Networks (GIAN) to promote research in India.\n\nHowever, the Jawahar Lal University (JNU) recently decided to slash the research seats (M.Phil &amp; Ph.D) from 1234 to 194, a decline of 84 percent in 2017-18. This decision that, applies to all Universities, was in compliance of UGC guidelines that seek to restrict the number of research scholars a faculty member of a university, central or state, can supervise at a time.', 'Raise the standard of education to enhance global status by enhancing research in Indian Universities', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '510-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 16:26:12', '2017-05-19 10:56:12', '', 510, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/510-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(987, 3, '2017-05-19 16:31:14', '2017-05-19 11:01:14', '<a href="https://www.topuniversities.com/university-rankings/world-university-rankings/2016">Two Indian Universities</a> feature in top 200 in the year 2016, according to the QS World University Ranking, as against <a href="https://www.topuniversities.com/university-rankings/world-university-rankings/2013">none in 2013</a>. The BJP government has launched programs such as IMPRINT India, Uchhatar Avishkar Yojana (UAY) and Global Initiative of Academic Networks (GIAN) to promote research in India.\r\n\r\nHowever, the Jawahar Lal University (JNU) recently <a href="https://www.telegraphindia.com/1170322/jsp/nation/story_142010.jsp">decided to slash </a>the research seats (M.Phil &amp; Ph.D) from 1234 to 194, a decline of 84 percent in 2017-18. This decision, that applies to all Universities, was in compliance of<a href="http://www.ugc.ac.in/pdfnews/4952604_UGC-(M.PHIL.-PH.D-DEGREES)-REGULATIONS,-2016.pdf"> UGC guidelines</a> that seek to restrict the number of research scholars a faculty member of a university, central or state, can supervise at a time.', 'Raise the standard of education to enhance global status by enhancing research in Indian Universities', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '510-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 16:31:14', '2017-05-19 11:01:14', '', 510, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/510-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(988, 3, '2017-05-19 16:38:53', '2017-05-19 11:08:53', 'The <a href="http://www.ugc.ac.in/pdfnews/8457040_UGC_regulaion_regarding_DeemedUniversity-3rdAmend.pdf">UGC regulations were amended</a> in 2016 to specify the rules for appointment of Vice Chancellors at Universities. The reforms included setting up of a Search cum Selection Committee (SCSC) comprising of a nominee of the chancellor, a nominee of Board of Management and a nominee of the Central Government/ UGC.\n\nSince only the appointment process of the Vice-Chancellors has been amended not of Directors, Principals and Registrars who also form senior positions, the performance against this promise  have been made by the BJP government to procedures to appoint Directors, Principals and Registrars.\n\nIt deserves to be mentioned that multiple senior members including <a href="https://blogs.wsj.com/indiarealtime/2015/02/22/in-full-amartya-sens-nalanda-university-resignation-letter/">Dr. Amartya Sen</a> and <a href="http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/nalanda-university-chancellor-george-yeo-resigns-from-post-cites-attack-on-autonomy-as-reason-4394182/">George Deo</a> (Both from Nalanda University), <a href="http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/education/news/IIT-Delhi-director-RK-Shevgaonkar-quits-over-demand-for-Subramanian-Swamys-dues/articleshow/45663599.cms">RK Shevgaonkar</a> (IIT Delhi) and <a href="http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-others/anil-kakodkar-rebuts-smriti-irani-i-am-out-of-the-process/">Anil Kakodkar</a> (IIT Bombay) have resigned since 2014 citing attack on autonomy and disagreements with the BJP government amid other reasons.', 'The procedures to make appointments to senior positions shall be made transparent to enhance the credibility of Indian Universities', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '519-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 16:38:53', '2017-05-19 11:08:53', '', 519, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/519-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(989, 3, '2017-05-19 16:40:15', '2017-05-19 11:10:15', 'The <a href="http://www.ugc.ac.in/pdfnews/8457040_UGC_regulaion_regarding_DeemedUniversity-3rdAmend.pdf">UGC regulations were amended</a> in 2016 to specify the rules for appointment of Vice Chancellors at Universities. The reforms included setting up of a Search cum Selection Committee (SCSC) comprising of a nominee of the chancellor, a nominee of Board of Management and a nominee of the Central Government/ UGC.\r\n\r\nSince only the appointment process of the Vice-Chancellors has been amended not of Directors, Principals and Registrars who also form senior positions, the performance against this promise  have been made by the BJP government to procedures to appoint Directors, Principals and Registrars.\r\n\r\nIt deserves to be mentioned that multiple senior members including <a href="https://blogs.wsj.com/indiarealtime/2015/02/22/in-full-amartya-sens-nalanda-university-resignation-letter/">Dr. Amartya Sen</a> and <a href="http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/nalanda-university-chancellor-george-yeo-resigns-from-post-cites-attack-on-autonomy-as-reason-4394182/">George Deo</a> (Both from Nalanda University), <a href="http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/education/news/IIT-Delhi-director-RK-Shevgaonkar-quits-over-demand-for-Subramanian-Swamys-dues/articleshow/45663599.cms">RK Shevgaonkar</a> (IIT Delhi) and <a href="http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-others/anil-kakodkar-rebuts-smriti-irani-i-am-out-of-the-process/">Anil Kakodkar</a> (IIT Bombay) have resigned since 2014 citing attack on autonomy and disagreements with the BJP government amid other reasons.', 'The procedures to make appointments to senior positions shall be made transparent to enhance the credibility of Indian Universities', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '519-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 16:40:15', '2017-05-19 11:10:15', '', 519, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/519-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(990, 3, '2017-05-19 16:44:52', '2017-05-19 11:14:52', '<a href="https://www.ebasta.in/">E-Basta</a>, an app launched by the BJP government, is an app designed to reduce the burden of school bag of students and provide ease of access from anywhere. More than 1500 school level books are available on E-Basta.\n\nOnly <a href="http://img.asercentre.org/docs/Publications/ASER%20Reports/ASER%202016/Report%20sections/aser2016-nationalfindings.pdf">20% of schools</a> in India have access to a computer, according to a Pratham report published in 2016. The BJP government has allocated Rs. 311 crores for Computer Aided Learning during the 2016-17.\n\nNo framework has been published by the BJP government to integrate the app (E-basta) with the existing system iand therefore the performance against this promise has been classified as "Inadequate Progress".', 'Explore ways to reduce the daily burden of carrying books to school for children using technology', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '434-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 16:44:52', '2017-05-19 11:14:52', '', 434, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/434-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(991, 3, '2017-05-19 16:45:11', '2017-05-19 11:15:11', '<a href="https://www.ebasta.in/">E-Basta</a>, an app launched by the BJP government, is an app designed to reduce the burden of school bag of students and provide ease of access from anywhere. More than 1500 school level books are available on E-Basta.\r\n\r\nOnly <a href="http://img.asercentre.org/docs/Publications/ASER%20Reports/ASER%202016/Report%20sections/aser2016-nationalfindings.pdf">20% of schools</a> in India have access to a computer, according to a Pratham report published in 2016. The BJP government has allocated Rs. 311 crores for Computer Aided Learning during the 2016-17.\r\n\r\nNo framework has been published by the BJP government to integrate the app (E-basta) with the existing system in the absence of which the promise cannot be fulfilled. Therefore the performance against this promise has been classified as "Inadequate Progress".', 'Explore ways to reduce the daily burden of carrying books to school for children using technology', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '434-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 16:45:11', '2017-05-19 11:15:11', '', 434, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/434-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(992, 3, '2017-05-19 16:50:24', '2017-05-19 11:20:24', 'The BJP government <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=157488">launched </a><a href="http://ssashagun.nic.in/">Shagun </a>in January 2017 to monitor the state level progress of SSA in Elementary Education. However, the portal doesn''t have any real time data  with regard to implementation of Sarva Shiksha Abhiyan.\n\n<a href="http://164.100.78.75/">No real time data </a>is publicly available. No criteria for the performance audit has been laid out by the Ministry. Since the government has made only the portal live with regard to performance against this promise and no real time data available', 'Mechanism would be set up for a performance audit of Sarva Shiksha Abhiyan (SSA) by means of real-time information', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '396-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 16:50:24', '2017-05-19 11:20:24', '', 396, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/396-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(993, 3, '2017-05-19 16:50:59', '2017-05-19 11:20:59', 'The BJP government <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=157488">launched </a><a href="http://ssashagun.nic.in/">Shagun </a>in January 2017 to monitor the state level progress of SSA in Elementary Education. However, the portal doesn''t have any real time data  with regard to implementation of Sarva Shiksha Abhiyan.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://164.100.78.75/">No real time data </a>is publicly available. No criteria for the performance audit has been laid out by the Ministry. Since the government has made only the portal live with regard to performance against this promise, this is considered "Inadequate Progress" in the absence of any real time data available.', 'Mechanism would be set up for a performance audit of Sarva Shiksha Abhiyan (SSA) by means of real-time information', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '396-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 16:50:59', '2017-05-19 11:20:59', '', 396, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/396-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(994, 3, '2017-05-23 19:16:27', '2017-05-23 13:46:27', 'Gross Enrollment Ratio (GER) at the secondary level has improved from <a href="http://www.dise.in/Downloads/Publications/Documents/SecondaryFlash%20Statistics-2014-15.pdf"> 77% in 2013-14</a> to <a href="http://udise.in/Downloads/Publications/Documents/Secondary_Flash_Statistics-2015-16.pdf">80% in 2015-16</a>. In the same period, the number of secondary schools has increased by approximately 13 thousand from <a href="http://dise.in/Downloads/Publications/Documents/SecondaryFlash%20Statistics-2013-14.pdf">2.26 lakh</a> to <a href="http://dise.in/Downloads/Publications/Documents/SecondaryFlash%20Statistics-2013-14.pdf">2.39 lakh</a>.\n\nThe percentage of minority students (SCs/STs/OBCs/Muslims) has gone up from <a href="http://dise.in/Downloads/Publications/Documents/SecondaryFlash%20Statistics-2013-14.pdf">81% in 2013-14</a> to <a href="http://udise.in/Downloads/Publications/Documents/Secondary_Flash_Statistics-2015-16.pdf">83% in 2015-16</a>.\n\nSince, only an improvement of 3% has been made with another 20% of children still not enrolled in Secondary schools, the performance of the government against this promise has been classified as "Inadequate Prog\n\n(GER is the percentage of kids who are enrolled in school out of the number of kids from the age group which corresponds to the same level.)', 'Universalize secondary school education and skill development with a focus on rural, tribal and difficult areas', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '401-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-23 19:16:27', '2017-05-23 13:46:27', '', 401, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/401-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(995, 3, '2017-05-19 16:54:23', '2017-05-19 11:24:23', 'Beti Bachao Beti Padhao (BBBP) was launched in January 2015 to prevent gender-based sex-selective elimination, ensure protection and education of girl child. Under the scheme, awareness campaigns were launched in <a href="http://164.100.47.190/loksabhaquestions/annex/10/AU4241.pdf">161 selected districts</a>.\r\n\r\nThe funds released under the scheme increased from <a href="http://164.100.47.190/loksabhaquestions/annex/10/AU4241.pdf">Rs. 13 crore in 2014-15</a> to <a href="http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/90-of-beti-bachao-beti-padhao-funds-unutilised-parliamentary-panel/articleshow/57757976.cms">Rs. 59 crore in 2015-16</a>. However,  only Rs. 5 crore had been utilized out of the Rs. 43 crore (for 2016-17) till January 2017, according to a parliamentary panel report.\r\n\r\nSince not even the funds have been utilised by the government, this is considered "Inadequate Progress".', 'Help Girls to continue and complete school education', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '412-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 16:54:23', '2017-05-19 11:24:23', '', 412, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/412-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(996, 3, '2017-05-19 17:06:10', '2017-05-19 11:36:10', '5 modules were created on Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Deaf-Blindness and Hearing Impairment in collaboration with World Bank for teacher training to achieve inclusive education. The modules were unveiled in January 2017. At least <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=157488">2 workshops</a> on these modules have been conducted since then.\r\n\r\nHowever, no action plan has been developed to integrate these modules in the pedagogy of the teachers to implement the modules at the school level, the promise cannot be fulfilled.', 'Develop special pedagogy for differently-abled students', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '414-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 17:06:10', '2017-05-19 11:36:10', '', 414, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/414-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(997, 4, '2017-05-19 17:22:54', '2017-05-19 11:52:54', '<img class="wp-image-345 aligncenter" src="http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/1.jpg" alt="" width="269" height="341" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">On 16th May 2014, Bhartiya Janta Party (BJP) won the electoral vote and Narendra Modi took oath as 14th Prime Minister of India on 26th May 2014. Election Promises Tracker is a citizen initiative that tracks BJP government’s performance against the promises the party made to the electorate in the fields of Education, Health, Governance, Economy, Industries and Agriculture. The promises have, primarily,  been taken from BJP''s Lok Sabha 2014 Elections  Manifesto which can be accessed <a href="http://www.bjp.org/images/pdf_2014/full_manifesto_english_07.04.2014.pdf">here</a>. Please read our guidelines for categorization of promises <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B_n-00l3g0wkT0Z5Qzk5TkQ2X2s/view">here</a>. Write to anuragkundu@electionpromisestracker.in in case you observe any discrepancy</p>', 'Central-Government', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '356-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 17:22:54', '2017-05-19 11:52:54', '', 356, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/356-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(998, 4, '2017-05-19 17:24:05', '2017-05-19 11:54:05', '<img class="wp-image-345 aligncenter" src="http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/1.jpg" alt="" width="269" height="341" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">On 16th May 2014, Bhartiya Janta Party (BJP) won the electoral vote and Narendra Modi took oath as 14th Prime Minister of India on 26th May 2014. Election Promises Tracker is a citizen initiative that tracks BJP government’s performance against the promises the party made to the electorate in the fields of Education, Health, Governance, Economy, Industries and Agriculture. The promises have, primarily,  been taken from BJP''s Lok Sabha 2014 Elections Manifesto which can be accessed <a href="http://www.bjp.org/images/pdf_2014/full_manifesto_english_07.04.2014.pdf">here</a>. Please read our guidelines for categorization of promises <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B_n-00l3g0wkT0Z5Qzk5TkQ2X2s/view">here</a>. Write to anuragkundu@electionpromisestracker.in in case you observe any discrepancy</p>', 'Central-Government', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '356-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-19 17:24:05', '2017-05-19 11:54:05', '', 356, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/356-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(999, 7, '2017-05-20 11:48:46', '2017-05-20 06:18:46', '[caption id="" align="aligncenter" width="640"]<img class="size-medium" src="http://static.dnaindia.com/sites/default/files/styles/half/public/2016/06/02/466986-pulses-dna.jpg?itok=ZTPXdBNL" width="640" height="360" /> MSP[/caption]\r\n\r\nThe BJP government <a href="http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/msp-50-percent-more-than-agriculture-produce-s-cost-can-distort-market-115022001360_1.html">has not accepted</a> the Standing Committee recommendation of keeping MSP (Minimum Support Price) at least 50% more than the cost of production, saying doing so may distort the market.\r\n\r\nNo steps have been taken <a href="http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/telangana-urges-centre-to-link-mgnrega-to-agriculture/articleshow/58297144.cms">for linking MNREGA to agriculture.</a>', 'Ensure a minimum of 50% profit over the cost of production by revising the Minimum Support Price and increase farmer profitability by linking MNREGA to agriculture', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '662-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-20 11:48:46', '2017-05-20 06:18:46', '', 662, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/662-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1000, 3, '2017-05-21 01:37:37', '2017-05-20 20:07:37', 'Aam Aadmi Party surged to power with a decisive mandate of 67 seats out of 70 in February 2015. The Party called for alternative politics and made several commitments to the people of Delhi. Aam Aadmi Party has completed two years in governance on 14th February 2017.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nElection Promises Tracker is a citizen initiative that tracks governments’ performance against the promises the party made to the electorate in the fields of Education, Health, Governance, Transportation, Environment and Services like Energy, Water, Wi-Fi. The promises have, primarily, been taken from AAP''s Delhi 2015 Elections Manifesto which can be accessed <a href="http://www.aamaadmiparty.org/AAP-Manifesto-2015.pdf">here</a>. Please read our guidelines for categorization of promises <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B_n-00l3g0wkT0Z5Qzk5TkQ2X2s/view">here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe are still in process of researching and reviewing the status of promises in other sectors and therefore present to you the status of AAP government’s performance against their education sector promises. Stay tuned!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWrite to anuragkundu@electionpromisestracker.in in case you observe any discrepancy and write to Joinus@electionpromisestracker.in to volunteer with us.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'delhi-government', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '379-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-21 01:37:37', '2017-05-20 20:07:37', '', 379, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/379-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
