(1007, 3, '2017-05-21 17:53:44', '2017-05-21 12:23:44', 'BharatNet (earlier called  National Optical Fibre Network), a project initiated by UPA-II in the year 2011 has been commissioned in <a href="http://www.bbnl.nic.in/actgps.aspx?langid=1&amp;ls_id=9&amp;l_id=9">18,039 gram panchayats out of 2.5 lakh gram panchayats</a>. The programme aims to 100 Mbps bandwidth in all Gram Panchayats in the country.\r\n\r\nSince the project has been commissioned in 7% villages only, it has been classified under "Inadequate Progress" category.', 'Focus on increasing the penetration and usage of broadband across the country. Deployment of broadband in every village would be a thrust area', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '720-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-21 17:53:44', '2017-05-21 12:23:44', '', 720, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/720-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1008, 3, '2017-05-21 17:57:57', '2017-05-21 12:27:57', 'No steps have been taken thus far by Modi Government to eliminate criminals from electoral exercise. On the contrary, <a href="http://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/31-ministers-in-modi-govt-have-declared-criminal-cases-against-them/story-bHvyXaDmcK5voJsyqfLXcO.html">31% of BJP Government Ministers have criminal cases against them</a>. 18% face serious criminal charges such as attempt to murder, murder, rape, kidnapping and crime against women.\r\n\r\nSince no action has been initiated by BJP government in this regard, the performance of the government against this promise has been classified as "Yet to Start"', 'To initiate electoral reforms to eliminate criminals', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '696-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-21 17:57:57', '2017-05-21 12:27:57', '', 696, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/696-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1009, 3, '2017-05-21 18:37:16', '2017-05-21 13:07:16', 'The <a href="http://www.prsindia.org/uploads/media/Appropriation/Appropriation%20acts-as%20passed%20by%20LS.pdf">Appropriation Acts (Repeal) Act 2016 </a>has been approved by the President on 6th May 2016. It repeals 758 Appropriation Acts, including Appropriation Acts for the railways, passed during the period of 1950-2012.  In all, 1159 laws have been repealed.\n\nThe promise has been classified as "Fulfilled" for now because the promise says "periodically", this cannot be a one-time exercise.', 'Periodically review and refine/ scrap outdated laws', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '682-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-21 18:37:16', '2017-05-21 13:07:16', '', 682, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/682-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1010, 3, '2017-05-21 18:23:49', '2017-05-21 12:53:49', 'The <a href="http://www.prsindia.org/uploads/media/Appropriation/Appropriation%20acts-as%20passed%20by%20LS.pdf">Appropriation Acts (Repeal) Act 2016 </a>has been approved by the President on 6th May 2016. It repeals 758 Appropriation Acts, including Appropriation Acts for the railways, passed during the period of 1950-2012.  In all, 1159 laws have been repealed.\r\n\r\nThe promise has been classified as "Fulfilled" for now because the promise says "periodically", this cannot be a one-time exercise.', 'Periodically review and refine/ scrap outdated laws', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '682-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-21 18:23:49', '2017-05-21 12:53:49', '', 682, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/682-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1011, 3, '2017-05-21 18:40:13', '2017-05-21 13:10:13', 'The promise is misplaced and reflects ignore since the E-Courts project <a href="http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/E-courts-to-reduce-pendency-in-a-big-way/articleshow/15381178.cms">had already started in 2007</a>. It aimed to make 14,249 courts ICT enabled by 2014 had already achieved a target of 8,000 by September 2011 and another 4,000 was expected by  2014. The project continues to progress at the same speed and there has been <a href="http://planningcommission.nic.in/aboutus/committee/wrkgrp12/wg_law.pdf">no increase in allocation</a> for this project by Government of India in the last three years.  The allocation for the project is Rs 1670 crores in the Five Year Plan (2012-17).', 'Initiate the computerization and networking of courts all over the country', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '675-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-21 18:40:13', '2017-05-21 13:10:13', '', 675, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/675-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1012, 3, '2017-05-21 22:21:25', '2017-05-21 16:51:25', 'The Delhi Government instituted Centralised Online System for Nursery/KG/First admission for children belonging to Economically Weaker Section (EWS) and Socially Disadvantaged Group (DG). This has eliminated any corruption and potential violations of the law from the admission process. Consequently, the schools’ compliance has improved from a meagre 37% in the previous year to nearly 100% during AAP rule. <sup><a href="http://edustud.nic.in/mis/studentadmission/webform1.aspx">1</a></sup> <sup><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/0By8GQpYPGNt7dFVvZktRVVlzN2s/view">2</a></sup>', 'Institute a centralized online system for nursery admissions, removing avenues for corruption.', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '716-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-21 22:21:25', '2017-05-21 16:51:25', '', 716, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/716-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1013, 7, '2017-05-22 02:15:12', '2017-05-21 20:45:12', 'Ministry of Health and Family Welfare (MoHFW) had put <a href="http://mohfw.nic.in/showfile.php?lid=3099">the concept note</a> on National eHealth Authority (NeHA) on March, 2015. It also had a <a href="http://mohfw.nic.in/showfile.php?lid=4000">consultation meeting</a> on setting up of NeHA in April, 2016. However, <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=154775">no further </a><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=154775">progress</a> has been made.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nIndia’s move to notify the Electronic Health Records standards in 2013 was a progress towards digitisation of healthcare. Establishment of a statutory authority, NeHA, could have been a key step to leverage telemedicine and mobile healthcare', 'Set up the ''National eHealth Authority'' to leverage telemedicine and mobile healthcare', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '597-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-22 02:15:12', '2017-05-21 20:45:12', '', 597, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/597-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1014, 7, '2017-05-22 02:15:20', '2017-05-21 20:45:20', 'Ministry of Health and Family Welfare (MoHFW) had put <a href="http://mohfw.nic.in/showfile.php?lid=3099">the concept note</a> on National eHealth Authority (NeHA) on March, 2015. It also had a <a href="http://mohfw.nic.in/showfile.php?lid=4000">consultation meeting</a> on setting up of NeHA in April, 2016. However, <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=154775">no further </a><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=154775">progress</a> has been made.\r\n\r\nIndia’s move to notify the Electronic Health Records standards in 2013 was a progress towards digitisation of healthcare. Establishment of a statutory authority, NeHA, could have been a key step to leverage telemedicine and mobile healthcare', 'Set up the ''National eHealth Authority'' to leverage telemedicine and mobile healthcare', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '597-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-22 02:15:20', '2017-05-21 20:45:20', '', 597, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/597-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1016, 3, '2017-05-23 19:16:30', '2017-05-23 13:46:30', 'Gross Enrollment Ratio (GER) at the secondary level has improved from <a href="http://www.dise.in/Downloads/Publications/Documents/SecondaryFlash%20Statistics-2014-15.pdf"> 77% in 2013-14</a> to <a href="http://udise.in/Downloads/Publications/Documents/Secondary_Flash_Statistics-2015-16.pdf">80% in 2015-16</a>. In the same period, the number of secondary schools has increased by approximately 13 thousand from <a href="http://dise.in/Downloads/Publications/Documents/SecondaryFlash%20Statistics-2013-14.pdf">2.26 lakh</a> to <a href="http://dise.in/Downloads/Publications/Documents/SecondaryFlash%20Statistics-2013-14.pdf">2.39 lakh</a>.\r\n\r\nThe percentage of minority students (SCs/STs/OBCs/Muslims) has gone up from <a href="http://dise.in/Downloads/Publications/Documents/SecondaryFlash%20Statistics-2013-14.pdf">81% in 2013-14</a> to <a href="http://udise.in/Downloads/Publications/Documents/Secondary_Flash_Statistics-2015-16.pdf">83% in 2015-16</a>.\r\n\r\nSince, only an improvement of 3% has been made with another 20% of children still not enrolled in Secondary schools, the performance of the government against this promise has been classified as "Inadequate Progress"\r\n\r\n(GER is the percentage of kids who are enrolled in school out of the number of kids from the age group which corresponds to the same level.)', 'Universalize secondary school education and skill development with a focus on rural, tribal and difficult areas', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '401-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-23 19:16:30', '2017-05-23 13:46:30', '', 401, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/401-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1017, 3, '2017-05-23 19:21:39', '2017-05-23 13:51:39', 'No new program has been started by the BJP government for modernisation of madrasas. Scheme for Providing Quality Education in Madrasas (SPQEM) has been running <a href="http://mhrd.gov.in/sites/upload_files/mhrd/files/lu1717.pdf">since 2008-2009</a>. The scheme is a demand driven scheme and expenditure depend on proposals from the state governments. Spending for SPQEM in 2015-16 increased to Rs 294 crore from Rs 108 crore in 2014-15. However, the funding for the program was slashed from <a href="http://indianexpress.com/article/education/no-english-medium-madrasas-as-yet-rs-294-5-crore-spent-on-modernisation/">182 crore to 108 crore. </a>The number of madrasas covered under the scheme has gone up from 15,000 in 2013-14 to 21,000 in 2015-16.\n\nHowever, with around <a href="http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/3ts-to-encourage-madrassas-to-teach-regular-subjects-too/articleshow/57821271.cms">70,000 madrasas</a> in the country, only 30% are being covered under SPQEM. No information could be found about the spending and number of madrasas covered from 2016-17.\n\nIn the light of the fact that no new program has been initated by BJonly 30% Madrasas are covered under the scheme,', 'Start a national modernization program for madrasas', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '420-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-23 19:21:39', '2017-05-23 13:51:39', '', 420, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/420-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1018, 3, '2017-05-23 19:20:35', '2017-05-23 13:50:35', 'No new program has been started by the BJP government for modernisation of madrasas. Scheme for Providing Quality Education in Madrasas (SPQEM) has been running <a href="http://mhrd.gov.in/sites/upload_files/mhrd/files/lu1717.pdf">since 2008-2009</a>. The scheme is a demand driven scheme and expenditure depend on proposals from the state governments. Spending for SPQEM in 2015-16 increased to Rs 294 crore from Rs 108 crore in 2014-15. However, the funding for the program was slashed from <a href="http://indianexpress.com/article/education/no-english-medium-madrasas-as-yet-rs-294-5-crore-spent-on-modernisation/">182 crore to 108 crore. </a>The number of madrasas covered under the scheme has gone up from 15,000 in 2013-14 to 21,000 in 2015-16.\r\n\r\nHowever, with around <a href="http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/3ts-to-encourage-madrassas-to-teach-regular-subjects-too/articleshow/57821271.cms">70,000 madrasas</a> in the country, only 30% are being covered under SPQEM. No information could be found about the spending and number of madrasas covered from 2016-17.', 'Start a national modernization program for madrasas', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '420-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-23 19:20:35', '2017-05-23 13:50:35', '', 420, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/420-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1019, 3, '2017-05-23 19:22:22', '2017-05-23 13:52:22', 'No new program has been started by the BJP government for modernisation of madrasas. Scheme for Providing Quality Education in Madrasas (SPQEM) has been running <a href="http://mhrd.gov.in/sites/upload_files/mhrd/files/lu1717.pdf">since 2008-2009</a>. The scheme is a demand driven scheme and expenditure depend on proposals from the state governments. Spending for SPQEM in 2015-16 increased to Rs 294 crore from Rs 108 crore in 2014-15. However, the funding for the program was slashed from <a href="http://indianexpress.com/article/education/no-english-medium-madrasas-as-yet-rs-294-5-crore-spent-on-modernisation/">182 crore to 108 crore. </a>The number of madrasas covered under the scheme has gone up from 15,000 in 2013-14 to 21,000 in 2015-16.\r\n\r\nHowever, with around <a href="http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/3ts-to-encourage-madrassas-to-teach-regular-subjects-too/articleshow/57821271.cms">70,000 madrasas</a> in the country, only 30% are being covered under SPQEM. No information could be found about the spending and number of madrasas covered from 2016-17.\r\n\r\nIn the light of the fact that no new program has been initiated by BJP government or revamped the previous one that now covers only 30% Madrasas, the performance of the government is classified as "Inadequate Progress"', 'Start a national modernization program for madrasas', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '420-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-23 19:22:22', '2017-05-23 13:52:22', '', 420, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/420-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1020, 3, '2017-05-23 19:24:39', '2017-05-23 13:54:39', '<a href="http://midh.gov.in/">Mission for Integrated Development of Horticulture (MIDH)</a> was launched by the UPA government to integrate all the schemes on horticulture. National Mission on Horticulture, launched under UPA, has been allocated <a href="http://164.100.47.193/lsscommittee/Agriculture/16_Agriculture_35.pdf">Rs. 2300 crores in 2017-18</a>, up from Rs. 1600 crores in 2016-17. However, no data of beneficiaries is available.\r\n\r\nUnder MIDH, <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/erelcontent.aspx?relid=113416">financial assistance</a> is also provided for Beekeeping for pollination and <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=158201">Floriculture</a>. The BJP government increased the FDI limit for Pisciculture, Aquaculture, Apiculture to <a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=149381">100% in 2016</a>.\r\n\r\nHowever, the horticulture production of the country rose marginally by 0.3% from <a href="http://164.100.47.190/loksabhaquestions/annex/11/AU3216.pdf">286 million tonnes in 2015-16 to 287 million tonnes in 2016-17</a>.', 'Promote horticulture, floriculture, pisciculture, bee-keeping and poultry for generating jobs and income for rural India', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '671-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-23 19:24:39', '2017-05-23 13:54:39', '', 671, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/671-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
