(1040, 3, '2017-05-27 15:29:21', '2017-05-27 09:59:21', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">The ‘zero defect , zero effect’ (ZED) scheme was launched in </span><a href="http://www.tribuneindia.com/news/punjab/community/pm-launches-national-sc-st-hub-zed-scheme-in-ludhiana/311368.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">October 2016</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. It is aimed to create a spirit of competition among enterprises for producing top quality products, as rated SMEs will get better business opportunities. The scheme plans to assist and rate 22,000 MSMEs on voluntary basis.  </span>\n\n<a href="http://164.100.47.5/newcommittee/reports/EnglishCommittees/Committee%20on%20Industry/280.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">No details</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> have been provided regarding availability of technological resources, institutional architecture, financial resources required or the parameters fixed for selection of the intended beneficiaries.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The official website doesn’t display any information regarding </span><a href="http://zed.org.in/awareness-and-training.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">trainings conducted</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> so far, or any information about how many </span><a href="http://www.zed.org.in/zed-certified-companies.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">certified MSMEs</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> are there.</span>\n\nSince there is no information t provided, this promise has been given the status of "Inadequate Progress".', 'Focus on Zero defect products', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '393-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-27 15:29:21', '2017-05-27 09:59:21', '', 393, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/393-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1041, 3, '2017-05-27 15:31:02', '2017-05-27 10:01:02', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">The ‘zero defect , zero effect’ (ZED) scheme was launched in </span><a href="http://www.tribuneindia.com/news/punjab/community/pm-launches-national-sc-st-hub-zed-scheme-in-ludhiana/311368.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">October 2016</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. It is aimed to create a spirit of competition among enterprises for producing top quality products, as rated SMEs will get better business opportunities. The scheme plans to assist and rate 22,000 MSMEs on voluntary basis.  </span>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://164.100.47.5/newcommittee/reports/EnglishCommittees/Committee%20on%20Industry/280.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">No details</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> have been provided regarding availability of technological resources, institutional architecture, financial resources required or the parameters fixed for selection of the intended beneficiaries.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The official website doesn’t display any information regarding </span><a href="http://zed.org.in/awareness-and-training.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">trainings conducted</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> so far, or any information about how many </span><a href="http://www.zed.org.in/zed-certified-companies.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">certified MSMEs</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> are there.</span>\r\n\r\nSince no information has been provided to analyse the performance, this promise has been given the status of "Inadequate Progress".', 'Focus on Zero defect products', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '393-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-27 15:31:02', '2017-05-27 10:01:02', '', 393, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/393-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1042, 3, '2017-05-27 17:35:23', '2017-05-27 12:05:23', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">The BJP government introduced Sagarmala Project which will promote port-led direct and indirect development and to provide infrastructure to transport goods to and from ports quickly. It received </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=117691"><span style="font-weight: 400;">in-principle</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> approval of the Cabinet in March, 2015. The </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=138881"><span style="font-weight: 400;">National Perspective Plan</span></a> <span style="font-weight: 400;">detailing the contours of the project was released in April 2016.</span>\n\nRs. 390 crores have been released for 35 projects taken up in 2015-16 &amp;  2016-17 financial years.\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Rs.3,34,000 crores are needed from 2017-19, however, </span><a href="http://164.100.47.5/newcommittee/reports/EnglishCommittees/Committee%20on%20Transport,%20Tourism%20and%20Culture/247.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">details about financing of the project </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">are not yet clear.</span>\n\nSince only the approval &amp; funds have been released, there is no progress that has been seen on the ground &amp; hence it has been given the status', 'Build world class Ports; connecting them with roads and rail to the hinterland so as to drive the maritime trade of the country', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '410-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-27 17:35:23', '2017-05-27 12:05:23', '', 410, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/410-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
