(1048, 3, '2017-05-27 17:39:06', '2017-05-27 12:09:06', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">The </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=108141"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Export Promotion Mission</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, proposed in budget,  2014-15, has seen no headway yet. It does not find a reference even in </span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="http://dgft.gov.in/exim/2000/ftp2015-20E.pdf">Foreign Trade Policy, 2015-20</a>.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The Export Promotion Mission is aimed at bringing the States on board to achieve India’s export target. It would provide the institutional frameworks for working with the State governments to boost India’s exports, according to the </span><a href="http://howtoexportimport.com/UserFiles/Windows-Live-Writer/83b5e694b628_101D2/FTP%202015-20%20statement.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Foreign Trade Policy statement</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The BJP government in its </span><a href="http://www.financialexpress.com/economy/narendra-modi-govt-unveils-its-first-trade-policy-targets-900-bn-in-exports/59535/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Foreign Trade Policy, 2015-20</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> has set an export target of Rs. 90,000 crores by 2020. However, no reference was made to Export Promotion Mission in its</span><a href="http://dgft.gov.in/exim/2000/ftp2015-20E.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> policy document</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Hence, this promise fall under "Yet to start" category.</span>', 'An Export Promotion Mission will be established integrating all Stakeholders', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '417-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-27 17:39:06', '2017-05-27 12:09:06', '', 417, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/417-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1049, 3, '2017-05-27 17:44:04', '2017-05-27 12:14:04', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">India’s rank in </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">‘Ease of Doing Business</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;">’ improved from </span><a href="http://www.thehindu.com/business/Economy/India-up-one-position-in-WB-ease-of-business-ranking/article16081515.ece"><span style="font-weight: 400;">142nd rank in 2014</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to </span><a href="http://www.doingbusiness.org/rankings"><span style="font-weight: 400;">130th rank in 2016</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, according to World Bank.  This is an improvement of 12 places.  However, on the parameter of ‘</span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Starting A New Business</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;">’, India’s rank slipped to </span><a href="http://www.doingbusiness.org/rankings"><span style="font-weight: 400;">155th rank in 2016</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> compared to </span><a href="http://www.business-standard.com/article/economy-policy/india-moves-up-by-just-one-notch-on-world-bank-s-ease-of-doing-business-index-116102501493_1.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">151th rank in 2014</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">On the parameter of ‘</span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Getting Electricity</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;">’ , India’s rank has been </span><a href="http://164.100.47.194/Loksabha/Questions/QResult15.aspx?qref=50242&amp;lsno=16"><span style="font-weight: 400;">improved </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">from 137th rank in 2015 to 26th rank in 2016. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">The report has recognized the efforts of getting electricity in Delhi to make it faster and cheaper to obtain an electricity connection.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The government </span><a href="http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/economy/policy/industrial-licence-validity-extended-to-three-years/articleshow/37676645.cms"><span style="font-weight: 400;">extended</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> the validity of industrial licence to 3 years and the industrial licence for defense to 15 years in July, 2014.</span>\r\n\r\nSince, India''s rank has been improved up to 12 places &amp; has space for the improvement in other parameters too, it has been given the status "Adequate Progress".', 'Will ensure that a conducive, enabling environment is created making ''doing business'' in India easy', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '432-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-27 17:44:04', '2017-05-27 12:14:04', '', 432, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/432-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1050, 3, '2017-05-27 17:46:11', '2017-05-27 12:16:11', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government has simplified the procedures in four areas only out of 11 indicators set by World Bank. These include </span><a href="http://www.doingbusiness.org/reforms/overview/economy/india"><span style="font-weight: 400;">paying taxes easier</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> by introducing electronic system for paying employees contributions, </span><a href="http://www.doingbusiness.org/reforms/overview/economy/india"><span style="font-weight: 400;">trading across borders</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> by means of single electronic gateway, simplifying </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">the process for getting an electricity connection by eliminating the internal wiring inspection by the Electrical Inspectorate </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">and the process of starting a new business </span><a href="http://www.businessmirror.com.ph/government-rolls-out-simplified-business-application-procedure-across-agencies/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">reducing</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> procedural requirement of 34 days to 8 days.</span>\n\nThere is a lot of scope to simplify the procedures &amp; to remove the bottlenecks for making business', 'Will ensure cutting the red tape, simplify the procedures & remove the bottlenecks', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '436-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-27 17:46:11', '2017-05-27 12:16:11', '', 436, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/436-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1051, 3, '2017-05-27 17:47:22', '2017-05-27 12:17:22', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government has simplified the procedures in four areas only out of 11 indicators set by World Bank. These include </span><a href="http://www.doingbusiness.org/reforms/overview/economy/india"><span style="font-weight: 400;">paying taxes easier</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> by introducing electronic system for paying employees contributions, </span><a href="http://www.doingbusiness.org/reforms/overview/economy/india"><span style="font-weight: 400;">trading across borders</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> by means of single electronic gateway, simplifying </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">the process for getting an electricity connection by eliminating the internal wiring inspection by the Electrical Inspectorate </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">and the process of starting a new business </span><a href="http://www.businessmirror.com.ph/government-rolls-out-simplified-business-application-procedure-across-agencies/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">reducing</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> procedural requirement of 34 days to 8 days.</span>\r\n\r\nThere is still a lot of scope to simplify the procedures &amp; to remove the bottlenecks for making business easy. Hence, it has been given the status "Inadequate Progress".', 'Will ensure cutting the red tape, simplify the procedures & remove the bottlenecks', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '436-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-27 17:47:22', '2017-05-27 12:17:22', '', 436, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/436-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
