(1054, 3, '2017-05-27 18:00:48', '2017-05-27 12:30:48', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">The </span><a href="https://www.pressreader.com/india/economic-times/20170311/281689729613269"><span style="font-weight: 400;">average delay</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in grant of environmental clearance is 238 days under BJP government (it was 316 in 2014) as compared to stipulated 105 days, according to March 2017 </span><a href="http://www.cag.gov.in/sites/default/files/audit_report_files/Executive_Summary_Union_Government_Report_39_of_2016.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">CAG Report.</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Only 11% projects have been granted environmental clearances under bounded time. </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">A National Regulator to oversee the entire process of grant of Environmental Clearance and monitoring is </span><a href="http://www.cag.gov.in/sites/default/files/audit_report_files/Executive_Summary_Union_Government_Report_39_of_2016.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">yet to be appointed</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> despite directions of the Supreme Court, the report further stated.</span>\n\nThough there has been a significant improvement in granting environmental clearances under BJP, there is a lot of scope to make the system transparent as directed by Supreme Court. Hence, given the status "Inadequate Progress".', 'Decision-making on environment clearances will be made transparent as well as time-bound', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '470-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-27 18:00:48', '2017-05-27 12:30:48', '', 470, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/470-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
