(1064, 3, '2017-05-27 18:12:15', '2017-05-27 12:42:15', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">No concrete action has been taken towards interest rate rationalisation. Raghuram Rajan, former RBI Governor, </span><a href="http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/opinion/editorial/monetary-relics/article6033883.ece"><span style="font-weight: 400;">proposed</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> rationalisation of interest rates by </span><a href="http://www.financialexpress.com/economy/budget-2017-must-revive-demand-re-fuel-industrial-activity/479963/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">removing</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Statutory Liquidity Ratio(SLR)/ Cash Reserve Ration (CRR) obligations of banks. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">An</span><a href="http://ficci.in/SEDocument/20399/MANUFACTURING-SURVEY-REPORT-March-2017.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> improvement</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> of 0.5% in average interest rate in manufacturing sector has been</span><a href="http://ficci.in/Sedocument/20374/MANUFACTURING-SURVEY-REPORT-August-2016.pdf"> <span style="font-weight: 400;">observed</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, according to FICCI March 2017 report. These rates, however, go as high as 15% in some cases, which suggests that no rationalisation of these rates has been done.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">(SLR/CRR are the obligations on Banks to reserve certain proportions of their deposits either in the form of gold, cash or other approved securities.)</span>\r\n\r\nAs the credit to the industry is still fluctuating &amp; no rationalization has been seen, it has been given the status "Inadequate Progress".', 'Take steps for Interest rate rationalization for credit to the industry', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '501-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-27 18:12:15', '2017-05-27 12:42:15', '', 501, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/501-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1065, 3, '2017-05-27 18:16:35', '2017-05-27 12:46:35', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">In the Union Budget 2017-18, the key ministries and departments(Ministry of Science and Technology, Department of Atomic Energy, etc), involved in research and development have </span><a href="https://thewire.in/105887/research-budget-biotech-iiser/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">received</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> a total of 34,700 crores, an increase of 11 % from the previous year. The increment in R&amp;D budget is a welcome step, however total R&amp;D spending of India </span><a href="https://www.iriweb.org/sites/default/files/2016GlobalR%26DFundingForecast_2.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">amounts to 0.85% of its GDP</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, while countries like Israel spend more than 4% of their GDP on R&amp;D.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP Government proposed to </span><a href="http://indiabudget.nic.in/ub2017-18/cen/dojstru2.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">repeal R&amp;D cess act</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, 1986 in Budget 2017, removing the 5% R&amp;D cess on Industries.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=112836"><span style="font-weight: 400;">announced</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">  National Manufacturing Competitiveness Programme (NMCP) in 2014. With an allocation of around 3,300 crores in the  2014-15 &amp; 3,000 crores in the year 2016, Government has </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=160776"><span style="font-weight: 400;">implemented various schemes</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> like Lean Manufacturing Competitiveness Scheme, Promotion of ICT in Manufacturing etc.</span>\r\n\r\nThough the funding has seen an increment, it is not sufficient keeping in view the inflation rate. Moreover, percentage budget of GDP has been constant  at 0.85%. Hence, it has been given status "Adequate Progress".', 'Increase the public spending on R&D and incentivize R&D investments by the industry to increase the competitiveness of the manufacturing sector', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '505-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-27 18:16:35', '2017-05-27 12:46:35', '', 505, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/505-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1066, 3, '2017-05-27 18:18:21', '2017-05-27 12:48:21', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">There was an </span><a href="http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/economy/foreign-trade/india-leads-fdi-in-south-asia-with-34-billion-investment-in-2014-report/articleshow/47806243.cms"><span style="font-weight: 400;">abnormal decrease</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> (in outward FDI investment in India) in 2013 because of macro-economic uncertainties when some of the Indian MNCs divested. But, now it is back on track.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> India outward investment (OFDI) </span><a href="http://www.newindianexpress.com/business/2017/jan/27/indias-investment-abroad-soars-but-still-behind-china-1563900.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">rose by 32%</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in 2016 as compared to 2015.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">RBI </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">has </span><a href="https://www.ibef.org/economy/indian-investments-abroad"><span style="font-weight: 400;">relaxed the norms</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> for domestic companies investing abroad by doing away with the ceiling for raising funds through pledge of shares, domestic and overseas assets. It </span><a href="http://www.entrepreneurscouncil.in/Indian-Investments-Abroad.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">raised the annual overseas investment</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> ceiling to US$ 125,000 from US$ 75,000 to establish joint ventures (JV) and wholly owned subsidiaries.</span>\n\nThere has been a significant improvement in outward FDI.H', 'Encourage Indian companies to go global and  support Indian companies in this endeavor', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '507-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-27 18:18:21', '2017-05-27 12:48:21', '', 507, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/507-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1067, 3, '2017-05-27 18:18:51', '2017-05-27 12:48:51', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">There was an </span><a href="http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/economy/foreign-trade/india-leads-fdi-in-south-asia-with-34-billion-investment-in-2014-report/articleshow/47806243.cms"><span style="font-weight: 400;">abnormal decrease</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> (in outward FDI investment in India) in 2013 because of macro-economic uncertainties when some of the Indian MNCs divested. But, now it is back on track.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> India outward investment (OFDI) </span><a href="http://www.newindianexpress.com/business/2017/jan/27/indias-investment-abroad-soars-but-still-behind-china-1563900.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">rose by 32%</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in 2016 as compared to 2015.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">RBI </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">has </span><a href="https://www.ibef.org/economy/indian-investments-abroad"><span style="font-weight: 400;">relaxed the norms</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> for domestic companies investing abroad by doing away with the ceiling for raising funds through pledge of shares, domestic and overseas assets. It </span><a href="http://www.entrepreneurscouncil.in/Indian-Investments-Abroad.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">raised the annual overseas investment</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> ceiling to US$ 125,000 from US$ 75,000 to establish joint ventures (JV) and wholly owned subsidiaries.</span>\r\n\r\nThere has been a significant improvement in outward FDI. Hence,  it has been given the status "Adequate Progress".', 'Encourage Indian companies to go global and  support Indian companies in this endeavor', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '507-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-27 18:18:51', '2017-05-27 12:48:51', '', 507, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/507-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1068, 3, '2017-05-27 23:45:07', '2017-05-27 18:15:07', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government set up Custom Clearance </span><a href="http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/govt-sets-up-ccfcs-at-ports-to-expedite-customs-clearance-115070700626_1.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Facilitation Centres</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> (CCFCs) at major Indian seaports &amp; Airports in July 2015 to ensure easier clearances. A </span><a href="http://www.cbec.gov.in/htdocs-cbec/customs/cs-circulars/cs-circulars-2015/circ-13-2015cs"><span style="font-weight: 400;">committee</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> was formed with immediate effect from April 2015. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">CBEC (Central Board of Excise &amp; Customs) launched Single window interface for facilitating Trade (</span><a href="http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/economy/indian-customs-launches-swift-clearances/article8426720.ece"><span style="font-weight: 400;">SWIFT</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">) in April 2016 for quick single window custom clearances  for import. The </span><a href="https://www.icegate.gov.in/SWIFT/index.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">portal</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> has been operational under CBEC website.</span>\r\n\r\nSince there has been an improvement in custom clearances after setting up felicitation centers, the progress has been classified as adequate.', 'Set up trade facilitation to ensure easier customs clearances', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '512-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-27 23:45:07', '2017-05-27 18:15:07', '', 512, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/512-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1069, 3, '2017-05-27 23:53:48', '2017-05-27 18:23:48', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">To promote bilateral cooperation with other countries, government has </span><a href="http://msme.gov.in/sites/default/files/IC_EN.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">continued International Cooperation Scheme</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in the 12th Year Plan with an outlay of Rs. 24 crores.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government</span><a href="http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/policy-trends/india-finalises-mou-on-msme-cooperation-with-iora-nations/articleshow/56687790.cms"> <span style="font-weight: 400;">finalised Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> on MSME corporations with Indian Ocean Rim Association (IORA) nations to share best practices &amp; innovation in January, 2017. It is yet to sign the MoU.</span>\n\nSince BJP has continued the previous scheme &amp; no other international cooperation', 'Provide international linkages for exports in MSME sector', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '515-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-27 23:53:48', '2017-05-27 18:23:48', '', 515, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/515-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1070, 3, '2017-05-27 23:55:01', '2017-05-27 18:25:01', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">To promote bilateral cooperation with other countries, government has </span><a href="http://msme.gov.in/sites/default/files/IC_EN.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">continued International Cooperation Scheme</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in the 12th Year Plan with an outlay of Rs. 24 crores.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government</span><a href="http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/policy-trends/india-finalises-mou-on-msme-cooperation-with-iora-nations/articleshow/56687790.cms"> <span style="font-weight: 400;">finalised Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> on MSME corporations with Indian Ocean Rim Association (IORA) nations to share best practices &amp; innovation in January, 2017. It is yet to sign the MoU.</span>\r\n\r\nSince BJP has continued only the previous scheme &amp; no other international linkages have been operational, the progress has been categorized as inadequate.', 'Provide international linkages for exports in MSME sector', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '515-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-27 23:55:01', '2017-05-27 18:25:01', '', 515, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/515-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
