(1072, 3, '2017-05-27 23:57:32', '2017-05-27 18:27:32', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">No dedicated bank has been set up for ensuring availability of credit for SMEs but the government has set up</span><a href="http://www.nsicffconline.in/"> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Finance Facilitation Centre</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> (an online portal) which allows MSMEs to apply for loans from various banks on NSIC Portal.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government has boosted up the</span><a href="https://www.cgtmse.in/"> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Credit Guarantee Scheme</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> set up in 2000, covering more than 5 lakhs guarantee approvals in the year 2015-16, which is the highest so far. It has registered a growth of about 28% over the previous Financial year.</span>\r\n\r\nThough no dedicated bank has been established, the government has taken significant measures to avail credit. Hence, this promise has been classified as adequate.', 'Ensure availability of credit through a dedicated SME bank', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '520-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-27 23:57:32', '2017-05-27 18:27:32', '', 520, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/520-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1073, 3, '2017-05-28 00:08:09', '2017-05-27 18:38:09', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government has </span><a href="http://www.dcmsme.gov.in/Revised%20Guidelines%20on%20ICT.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">revised the guidelines</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> for “Promotion of ICT in MSME sector” under which it has proposed the subsidy of 60%  for using Cloud Computing  for a period of 2 years. Budget </span><a href="http://164.100.47.5/newcommittee/reports/EnglishCommittees/Committee%20on%20Industry/280.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">allocation</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> for this scheme has been reduced from Rs. 18 crore in 2014 to Rs. 5 crores in 2017</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/backgrounders.aspx?relid=104383"><span style="font-weight: 400;">continued</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Bar-Code Scheme launched under UPA government to benefit MSMEs for inventory control, wide acceptability of products in the domestic and world markets &amp; higher efficiencies. A total expenditure for this scheme has been </span><a href="http://www.dcmsme.gov.in/schemes/assist_bar_code.htm"><span style="font-weight: 400;">increased</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> from 1.25 crore in 2014 to 1.54 crore in 2016.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Ministry of MSME launched </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=148729"><span style="font-weight: 400;">MSME Databank Portal</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in August, 2016 which will provide real time information on various types of the MSMEs registered. This has been done to boost up public procurement.</span>\n\nSince Budget allocation has been reduced by more than 70% &amp; no new scheme has been launched, this promise has been classified as iqqqqqnadequate', 'Ensure adoption of IT in MSMEs', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '523-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-28 00:08:09', '2017-05-27 18:38:09', '', 523, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/523-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1074, 3, '2017-05-28 00:08:24', '2017-05-27 18:38:24', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government has </span><a href="http://www.dcmsme.gov.in/Revised%20Guidelines%20on%20ICT.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">revised the guidelines</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> for “Promotion of ICT in MSME sector” under which it has proposed the subsidy of 60%  for using Cloud Computing  for a period of 2 years. Budget </span><a href="http://164.100.47.5/newcommittee/reports/EnglishCommittees/Committee%20on%20Industry/280.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">allocation</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> for this scheme has been reduced from Rs. 18 crore in 2014 to Rs. 5 crores in 2017</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/backgrounders.aspx?relid=104383"><span style="font-weight: 400;">continued</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Bar-Code Scheme launched under UPA government to benefit MSMEs for inventory control, wide acceptability of products in the domestic and world markets &amp; higher efficiencies. A total expenditure for this scheme has been </span><a href="http://www.dcmsme.gov.in/schemes/assist_bar_code.htm"><span style="font-weight: 400;">increased</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> from 1.25 crore in 2014 to 1.54 crore in 2016.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Ministry of MSME launched </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=148729"><span style="font-weight: 400;">MSME Databank Portal</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in August, 2016 which will provide real time information on various types of the MSMEs registered. This has been done to boost up public procurement.</span>\r\n\r\nSince Budget allocation has been reduced by more than 70% &amp; no new scheme has been launched, this promise has been classified as inadequate.', 'Ensure adoption of IT in MSMEs', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '523-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-28 00:08:24', '2017-05-27 18:38:24', '', 523, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/523-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1075, 3, '2017-05-28 00:19:44', '2017-05-27 18:49:44', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">The BJP government has</span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=116587"> <span style="font-weight: 400;">approved</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> setting up of “</span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Technology Centre Systems program</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;">” for MSMEs under which 15 new Technology Development Centers are proposed to be established, and the existing centers are proposed to be upgraded over next six years. The objective of these centres is to provide support to Electronics Systems Design &amp; Manufacturing. Construction for 4 such technology centers has been </span><a href="http://msme.gov.in/sites/default/files/Achievments_Brochure_Final__17-05-16_.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">started</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> so far.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government </span><a href="http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/budget-2015/student/Union-Budget-2015-Rs-150-crore-alloted-for-research-under-Atal-Innovation-Mission/articleshow/46413665.cms"><span style="font-weight: 400;">launched</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Atal Innovation Mission (AIM) in Budget 2015 with an allocation of Rs. 150 crores out of which only </span><a href="http://164.100.47.193/lsscommittee/Finance/16_Finance_48.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Rs. 16.8 crores have been used</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. In Budget 2017-18, allocation for this scheme has been </span><a href="http://164.100.47.193/lsscommittee/Finance/16_Finance_48.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">reduced</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to Rs. 112 crores.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">To promote innovation in MSMEs, 21 out of 80 </span><a href="http://www.pib.nic.in/newsite/mbErel.aspx?relid=133167"><span style="font-weight: 400;">promised</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> livelihood business incubators have been </span><a href="http://msme.gov.in/sites/default/files/Achievments_Brochure_Final__17-05-16_.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">approved</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> under the scheme ASPIRE launched in March, 2015. One such incubator has been set up in Deoria, U.P in April, 2015. Another incubators in Rajkot &amp; </span><a href="http://knnindia.co.in/news/newsdetails/msme/kalraj-mishra-inaugurates-livelihood-business-incubation-at-jamia-under-aspire"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Jamia</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> have been inaugurated in Dec, 2015 &amp; Nov., 2016 respectively.</span>\n\nSince the progress for proposed centres is very slow', 'Support in R&D and innovation in MSMEs', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '527-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-28 00:19:44', '2017-05-27 18:49:44', '', 527, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/527-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
