(1076, 3, '2017-05-28 00:20:53', '2017-05-27 18:50:53', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">The BJP government has</span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=116587"> <span style="font-weight: 400;">approved</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> setting up of “</span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Technology Centre Systems program</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;">” for MSMEs under which 15 new Technology Development Centers are proposed to be established, and the existing centers are proposed to be upgraded over next six years. The objective of these centres is to provide support to Electronics Systems Design &amp; Manufacturing. Construction for 4 such technology centers has been </span><a href="http://msme.gov.in/sites/default/files/Achievments_Brochure_Final__17-05-16_.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">started</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> so far.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government </span><a href="http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/budget-2015/student/Union-Budget-2015-Rs-150-crore-alloted-for-research-under-Atal-Innovation-Mission/articleshow/46413665.cms"><span style="font-weight: 400;">launched</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Atal Innovation Mission (AIM) in Budget 2015 with an allocation of Rs. 150 crores out of which only </span><a href="http://164.100.47.193/lsscommittee/Finance/16_Finance_48.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Rs. 16.8 crores have been used</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. In Budget 2017-18, allocation for this scheme has been </span><a href="http://164.100.47.193/lsscommittee/Finance/16_Finance_48.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">reduced</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to Rs. 112 crores.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">To promote innovation in MSMEs, 21 out of 80 </span><a href="http://www.pib.nic.in/newsite/mbErel.aspx?relid=133167"><span style="font-weight: 400;">promised</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> livelihood business incubators have been </span><a href="http://msme.gov.in/sites/default/files/Achievments_Brochure_Final__17-05-16_.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">approved</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> under the scheme ASPIRE launched in March, 2015. One such incubator has been set up in Deoria, U.P in April, 2015. Another incubators in Rajkot &amp; </span><a href="http://knnindia.co.in/news/newsdetails/msme/kalraj-mishra-inaugurates-livelihood-business-incubation-at-jamia-under-aspire"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Jamia</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> have been inaugurated in Dec, 2015 &amp; Nov., 2016 respectively.</span>\r\n\r\nSince the progress for proposed centres is very slow &amp; spending is not up to the mark, this promise has been classified as inadequate.', 'Support in R&D and innovation in MSMEs', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '527-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-28 00:20:53', '2017-05-27 18:50:53', '', 527, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/527-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
