lop high impact domains like Labour-intensive manufacturing (viz. textile, footwear, electronics assembly, etc.) and Tourism', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '534-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-28 00:27:50', '2017-05-27 18:57:50', '', 534, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/534-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1080, 3, '2017-05-28 00:29:02', '2017-05-27 18:59:02', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government </span><a href="http://www.livemint.com/Politics/rg9vnHs29V3bCYOD6jkJzJ/Budget-2017-Govt-to-unveil-scheme-for-leather-and-footwear.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">approved</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> a special package of 6,000 crores for the textiles &amp; apparel sector to create 1 crore jobs over next three years. This </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=146422"><span style="font-weight: 400;">scheme includes</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> bearing 12% Employer''s’ share under EPF for the new employees for first three years &amp; choice of optional EPF for employees earning less than 15,000.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">India significantly improved its Global Travel &amp; </span><a href="http://www.hindustantimes.com/business-news/india-jumps-12-spots-in-wef-s-global-travel-tourism-ranking/story-jQLwAXYwhgEVw0JrlDq6wJ.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Tourism ranking</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> from 52 in the year 2015 to 40 in the year 2017, an improvement by 12 positions, the World Economic Forum </span><a href="http://www3.weforum.org/docs/WEF_TTCR_2017_web_0401.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">reports</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Government of India </span><a href="http://www.financialexpress.com/india-news/five-significant-steps-taken-by-modi-government-to-promote-tourism-hospitality-sector/379469/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">launched Swadesh Darshan</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Scheme in January 2015 to develop theme based tourist circuits, 27 projects of 2,200 crores have been sanctioned so far.</span>\r\n\r\nSince the development can be measured by various indicators &amp; on the status of job creation, government has failed to provide sufficient progress. Though in tourism sector, it has done really good. Hence, the promise has been classified as adequate.', 'Strategically develop high impact domains like Labour-intensive manufacturing (viz. textile, footwear, electronics assembly, etc.) and Tourism', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '534-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-28 00:29:02', '2017-05-27 18:59:02', '', 534, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/534-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1081, 3, '2017-05-28 00:32:04', '2017-05-27 19:02:04', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government </span><a href="http://dipp.nic.in/English/Schemes/IIUS/IIUS_modified_01August2013.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">continued</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Modified Industrial Infrastructure Upgradation Scheme (MIIUS) under 12th year plan. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Under this Scheme, projects have been </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=156108"><span style="font-weight: 400;">undertaken to upgrade</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> infrastructure in existing Industrial Parks/ Estates/ Areas. This scheme was </span><a href="http://dipp.nic.in/English/Schemes/IIUS/IIUS_modified_01August2013.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">allocated</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Rs. 1030 crores &amp; the Central assistance of Rs. 513 crores has been </span><a href="http://dipp.nic.in/English/Schemes/IIUS/Progress_2017_18April2017.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">approved</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> under 12th year plan as of March, 2017 as </span><a href="http://dipp.nic.in/English/Schemes/IIUS/Progress_2017_18April2017.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">compared</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to allocated Rs. 1050 crores &amp; the central assistance of Rs. 378 crores under 11th year plan.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government </span><a href="http://www.financialexpress.com/budget/union-budget-2017-infrastructure-status-for-affordable-housing-to-boost-volume-of-construction-activities-experts/532352/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">launched</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">  “Housing for all by 2022” scheme under  Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (PMAY) </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">to boost affordable housing &amp; creating job potential through it.  While the target has been to construct 2 crore houses by 2022, a total of </span><a href="http://mhupa.gov.in/writereaddata/PMAY_Progress.pdf"><span style="font-weight: 400;">6716 houses</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> have been built as of December, 2016.</span>\r\n\r\nSince there hasn''t been a sufficient increase in budget allocation &amp; in terms of providing houses, government has not done well. Hence, the progress has been classified as inadequate.', 'Harness the opportunities provided by the upgradation of infrastructure and housing, for its job generating potential', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '538-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-28 00:32:04', '2017-05-27 19:02:04', '', 538, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/538-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1082, 3, '2017-05-28 00:40:55', '2017-05-27 19:10:55', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">In January, 2016, BJP government</span><a href="http://startupindia.gov.in/status.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> launched Start-Up India Action Plan</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to empower start-ups to grow and innovate. 932 Start-up applications have been approved so far.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government has </span><a href="http://www.financialexpress.com/budget/union-budget-2017-good-news-for-small-companies-now-pay-only-25-tax/532458/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">reduced the income tax</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> for the companies with an annual turnover of less than 50 lakhs to 25% from April,2017 in Budget 2017-18.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government is initiating a </span><a href="http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/governments-credit-guarantee-scheme-to-give-startups-a-loan-lifeline-of-up-to-rs-5-crore/articleshow/57610609.cms"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Credit Guarantee scheme</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to give start-ups a loan life of up to Rs. 5 Crore., awaiting Cabinet approval.</span>', 'Encourage and empower our youth for self-employment - incubating entrepreneurship as well as facilitating credit', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '541-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-28 00:40:55', '2017-05-27 19:10:55', '', 541, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/541-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1083, 3, '2017-05-28 00:41:04', '2017-05-27 19:11:04', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">In January, 2016, BJP government</span><a href="http://startupindia.gov.in/status.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> launched Start-Up India Action Plan</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to empower start-ups to grow and innovate. 932 Start-up applications have been approved so far.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government has </span><a href="http://www.financialexpress.com/budget/union-budget-2017-good-news-for-small-companies-now-pay-only-25-tax/532458/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">reduced the income tax</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> for the companies with an annual turnover of less than 50 lakhs to 25% from April,2017 in Budget 2017-18.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government is initiating a </span><a href="http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/governments-credit-guarantee-scheme-to-give-startups-a-loan-lifeline-of-up-to-rs-5-crore/articleshow/57610609.cms"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Credit Guarantee scheme</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to give start-ups a loan life of up to Rs. 5 Crore., awaiting Cabinet approval.</span>', 'Encourage and empower our youth for self-employment - incubating entrepreneurship as well as facilitating credit', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '541-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-28 00:41:04', '2017-05-27 19:11:04', '', 541, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/541-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1084, 3, '2017-05-28 00:43:46', '2017-05-27 19:13:46', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government </span><a href="http://www.financialexpress.com/economy/employment-opportunities-to-1-crore-youth-by-2020-bandaru-dattatreya/517086/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">decided</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to transform 100 Employment Exchanges out of 978 existing centres into </span><a href="http://www.mcc-centre.com/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Model Career Centres</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> (MCC). </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Government </span><a href="http://www.business-standard.com/article/government-press-release/upgradation-of-employment-exchanges-117020800698_1.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">provides financial assistance</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to these centres upto Rs 50 lakh per centre based on the proposals and scheme guidelines. The Centre has already </span><a href="http://www.business-standard.com/article/economy-policy/coming-soon-model-career-centres-for-jobseekers-116012600013_1.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">allocated money</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to states for 70 such centres. The portal provides the data only for three such centres at Gurgaon, Mumbai and Chennai.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Ministry of Labour &amp; Employment launched National Career Center (NCS) </span><a href="https://www.ncs.gov.in/Pages/default.aspx"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Portal</span></a> <span style="font-weight: 400;">to transform the existing National Employment Service &amp; </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/printrelease.aspx?relid=161407"><span style="font-weight: 400;">linking all employment exchanges</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> of the country. The Centre partly funded the IT upgradation for this initiative.</span>\n\nSince only three such centres, the progress has been classified as inadequate.', 'Transform our Employment Exchanges into Career Centres - connecting our youth with job opportunities as well as providing counselling and training', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '544-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-05-28 00:43:46', '2017-05-27 19:13:46', '', 544, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/544-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1085, 3, '2017-05-28 00:45:00', '2017-05-27 19:15:00', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">BJP government </span><a href="http://www.financialexpress.com/economy/employment-opportunities-to-1-crore-youth-by-2020-bandaru-dattatreya/517086/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">decided</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to transform 100 Employment Exchanges out of 978 existing centres into </span><a href="http://www.mcc-centre.com/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Model Career Centres</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> (MCC). </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Government </span><a href="http://www.business-standard.com/article/government-press-release/upgradation-of-employment-exchanges-117020800698_1.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">provides financial assistance</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to these centres upto Rs 50 lakh per centre based on the proposals and scheme guidelines. The Centre has already </span><a href="http://www.business-standard.com/article/economy-policy/coming-soon-model-career-centres-for-jobseekers-116012600013_1.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">allocated money</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to states for 70 such centres. The portal provides the data only for three such centres at Gurgaon, Mumbai and Chennai.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Ministry of Labour &amp; Employment launched National Career Center (NCS) </span><a href="https://www.ncs.gov.in/Pages/default.aspx"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Portal</span></a> <span style="font-weight: 400;">to transform the existing National Employment Service &amp; </span><a href="http://pib.nic.in/newsite/printrelease.aspx?relid=161407"><span style="font-weight: 400;">linking all employment exchanges</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> of the country. The Centre partly funded the IT upgradation for this initiative.</span>\r\n\r\nSince information for only three such centres has been given &amp; the progress is very slow, the progress has been classified as inadequate.', 'Transform our Employment Exchanges into Career Centres - connecting our youth with job opportunities as well as providing counselling and training', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '544-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-28 00:45:00', '2017-05-27 19:15:00', '', 544, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/544-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1086, 3, '2017-05-29 01:13:45', '2017-05-28 19:43:45', 'BharatNet (earlier called  National Optical Fibre Network), a project initiated by UPA-II in the year 2011 has been commissioned in <a href="http://www.bbnl.nic.in/actgps.aspx?langid=1&amp;ls_id=9&amp;l_id=9">18,039 gram panchayats out of 2.5 lakh gram panchayats</a>. The programme aims to provide 100 Mbps bandwidth in all Gram Panchayats in the country.\r\n\r\nSince the project has been commissioned in 7% villages only, it has been classified under "Inadequate Progress" category.', 'Focus on increasing the penetration and usage of broadband across the country. Deployment of broadband in every village would be a thrust area', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '720-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-29 01:13:45', '2017-05-28 19:43:45', '', 720, 'http://www.electionpromisestracker.in/720-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
